title: speedy chop suey
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot shortening in pressure cooker.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cook at 10 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.
Release pressure under cold running water.
Add onion and celery.
Cook for 2 more minutes at 10 pounds pressure. Again, release pressure.
Add undrained mushrooms to mixture.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch and slowly stir into mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add drained bean sprouts. Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, pour in 1 cup rice, then add mushroom soup and milk (save a little to pour over chicken).
Then sprinkle package dry onion soup over rice and soup-milk mixture.
Layer chicken breasts over this and add the remaining soup and milk and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This is good served with small salad.
This will serve 4 to 6 people.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots 7 minutes; drain.
Add to onion and green pepper. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Chill.

title: p'nutty chicken salad crepes
directions: Combine chicken, eggs, water chestnuts, bell pepper, onions and 1/2 cup peanuts.
Mix mayonnaise with seasonings.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss.
Place in Pyrex dish in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Spoon into crepes, fold and place on platter.
Pour sauce over the top.
Garnish with grated cheese, pepper, cherry tomatoes, parsley and chopped peanuts.

title: herb rice
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Stir; cover and cook over low heat for 14 minutes or until tender.
I often use Minute rice.
If you do, place all ingredients except the rice into 2 cups water and bring to a boil.
Add rice; stir, cover and let stand until all water is absorbed by the rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan on the stove.
Bring to a boil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all.
Drop onto waxed paper and place in refrigerator to harden.

title: snickers pie
directions: Using a microwave-safe bowl, melt candy bars and half and half. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Allow to thaw 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and add butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate and form "crust".
Microwave for 2 minutes, uncovered, on High speed.

title: broiled beef sandwiches
directions: Toast bread on one side.
Spread butter and mustard on toasted side. Spread beef mixture on untoasted side of bread covering entire slice.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients together to rolling boil.
Boil over medium heat (for simmering); constantly stir.
Remove from heat.
Melt chocolate pieces.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Let cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: potato salad
directions: Brown bacon, drain.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper, mustard, eggs and cook 10 minutes.
Serve this dressing over mixture of crumbled bacon and diced potatoes.

title: moma's pecan pies
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and syrup.
Mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well after each.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Use two new 8-inch plastic flower pots or 3 (6-inch) pots.

title: bean dip
directions: Pick over and rinse pinto beans.
Place in a large saucepan. Add enough unsalted water to cover. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: pop's dixies
directions: Add sugar to melted margarine and butter; mix well. Beat in eggs and add salt.
Sift in flour and pecans.
Grease and flour a shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Enjoy!

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring, then sift twice more.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add whipping cream and remaining flour. Beat well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions, add 3 T. sour cream, blend in whipped topping.
Stir in drained pineapple chunks and sliced bananas.
Add vanilla wafers.
Place in bowl and garnish with remaining wafers.

title: fast and easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown meat in skillet; drain grease off, then add seasonings, tomato soup, sauce, paste and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In large, ungreased casserole or 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer sauce, noodles and sliced cheese.
Make another layer.
Place remaining meat sauce on top; cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until cheese is melted and a little brown.
Serves 6.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, one at a time, in large bowl. Pour into a large glass baking dish (ungreased).
Crush the corn flakes into crumbs and then mix with the margarine (3 tablespoons). Sprinkle this mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from the oven and let it set for another 15 minutes before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn on low.
Cook 7 to 8 hours.
They need no watching if heat is right.
My crock-pot takes longer.
I also add about 1 or 2 tablespoons of prepared mustard.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and enough water to cover in 4-quart pan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes, gradually stirring in salad dressing, cream cheese, onion powder, salt and pepper until light and fluffy.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until thoroughly heated.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together before you add the liquid.
Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and glaze.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Combine cooked wild rice with bacon, soup and water.
Save remainder of soup to add to mixture as desired.
Add carefully, so rice doesn't become mushy.
Combine with mushrooms and pour into baking dish.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°, or until top gets crusty and rice clings to spoon.

title: pat in pan pie crust
directions: In a pie plate mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add oil and milk. With a fork, work mixture into dough.
Press crust up sides and smooth out bottom.

title: sausage stew
directions: Cook all together, covered, until vegetables are done.

title: creamed beets
directions: Bring beets, water and salt to boiling.
Mix flour and milk. Pour in beets.
Let simmer.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl; refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables for dipping, e.g., carrots, green pepper slices, small tomatoes, cauliflower, celery sticks, broccoli, cucumber, etc.

title: brownies for the crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts, stir in nuts last. Pour into 13 x 9 greased pan and bake in 350 degree preheated oven for 40-45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Place in a casserole and top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: In large casserole dish, place milk, salt and butter. Microwave on High 3 1/2 minutes until mixture boils.
Add rice and stir.
Cover and cook on High for 30 seconds, allowing mixture to return to a boil.
Reduce to simmer (low) for 10 minutes.
Stir and simmer 5 to 7 minutes more.
Test rice for doneness. Sprinkle with granulated brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Blend together the ingredients to make marinade.
Cover a London broil with marinade and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Cover with foil or wrap while marinating.
Barbecue London broil over medium heat, 5 to 10 minutes per side.
Cut on the diagonal.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes and melt in a pot, stirring constantly. Add chili to taste. Mix well. Serve with chips.

title: fruited burgundy
directions: Combine sugar and fruit in large pitcher; mix well, then add chopped ice.
Add sparkling Burgundy and serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: hazelnut chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to batter.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Remove to a wire rack to cool.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir Crispix with peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Put powdered sugar in bag (one cup at a time) and put Crispix in bag (one cup at a time).
Shake until well coated.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: pear blondies
directions: Combine sugar, egg, shortening and vanilla until well mixed. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir into batter.
Add pears and chocolate chips.

title: apple crisp
directions: Drain apples; place in buttered 9-inch shallow baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice and white sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple mixture. Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Meanwhile, chop onion and green pepper; brown in a large skillet with hamburger and season to taste.
Add drained corn, tomato paste and macaroni and cheese to hamburger; mix well.
Adjust seasonings.
Transfer to casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mango chutney
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until thick.
Pour into warmed jars and seal with wax. To warm jars, place on a cookie sheet in a warm (250°) oven until ready to fill.

title: walnut caramels
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with foil; lightly butter foil. In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, cream and butter. Cook over medium heat.
Stir with wooden spoon until temperature reaches 245°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Let cool thoroughly.
Cut into pieces and wrap in clear wrap or wax paper.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Mix half tub of icing with drop of yellow food coloring.
Mix half of tub of icing with drop of green food coloring.
Spread yellow icing on flat side of half of the vanilla wafers.
Spread green icing on the flat side of the other half of the vanilla wafers.
Put 1 yellow and 1 green iced vanilla wafer on each side of an Oreo to make a sandwich.
Fix remainder of cookies the same way.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and cold water.
Set in refrigerator. Process apples, oranges, cranberries, nuts, pineapple and sugar in food processor.
Mix with jello mixture and pour into molds. Refrigerate until solid.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Serve cold.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Put into crock-pot; cook on low for 2 to 3 hours or you can bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egyptian beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight in the water with salt; or boil two minutes and soak one hour or longer.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce the heat.
Simmer gently until the beans are tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Drain the beans thoroughly and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix gently but thoroughly.
Chill.
At serving time, correct the seasonings and serve beans on romaine lettuce garnished with scallions.
Makes 4 hors d'oeuvre servings.

title: easy sopaipillas
directions: Tear or cut shells up as you wish.
Dip them in the deep fat fryer until brown.
Mix cinnamon and sugar or powdered sugar in small bowl.
Sprinkle on shells while hot.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix together and chill 1/2 hour.
Divide into 10 balls.
Roll out what you need and freeze the rest in a zip-loc bag for later use.

title: cabbage rolls(75 to 100)
directions: Note:
Ingredients may be chopped in food processor (just until chopped).

title: mini pizzas
directions: First, set the oven on 350°.
Place each muffin half face up on a cookie sheet.
Put a spoonful of tomato sauce on each muffin half.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Put the cookie sheet into the oven.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into individual servings.
Brown and season with salt.
Add flour to mustard and make paste.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well and pour over spareribs.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: noodle rice dish
directions: In large soup pot, melt butter; pour in noodles and brown until golden.
Add rice and mix thoroughly.
Combine all the rest of the ingredients and place in an oblong casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients with butter.
Sprinkle topping over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dredge chicken in salad dressing mix. Dip in mixture of margarine, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Arrange on baking pans and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Turn, sprinkle with paprika and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving 1 tablespoon of liquid.
Butter one-quart casserole and arrange 1/2 of asparagus on the bottom. Cover with sliced eggs.
Heat the soup with the seasoning.
Pour half over the eggs and sprinkle with 2/3 cup of grated cheese. Repeat with the asparagus, soup and cheese layer.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together at one time.
Wrap in towel until cool enough to knead.
Separate and add colors.

title: tassies
directions: Mix well, first with fork, then with hand.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian sweets
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, margarine and salt; mix well.
Place pineapple slices in buttered baking dish.
Top with potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with marshmallows; bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 5 to 10.

title: crock-pot apple pudding
directions: Beat sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add apples with dry ingredients and mix well.
Spray a 2-pound coffee can with cooking spray or grease and flour it well.
Pour batter into can, filling no more than 2/3 full.
Place can in crock-pot.
Do not add water.
Cover, but leave cover ajar so steam can escape.
Cook on High for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Don't peek before the last hour of baking.
Cake is done, when top is set.
Let stand in can for a few minutes before tipping pudding out on a plate.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and add all ingredients.
Mix well and form a ball.
Roll it in the chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in mixing bowl; mix well.
Place oleo, Crisco, oil, cocoa and water in medium saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Stir well and add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in an 11 x 16-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes and chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Pare potatoes and slice thinly. Place half of the potatoes in greased baking dish; sprinkle with half of the flour and soup mix.
Repeat.
Place chops on top.
Dot with butter; pour milk over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another half hour.
Serves 6.

title: church supper potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add onions.
Cook until clear.
Mix well with Cheddar cheese, soup and sour cream.
Crumble potatoes into mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: susan's green chile
directions: Brown pork dry in a nonstick pot.
Season well with salt, garlic salt and pepper.
When pork is just browned, add 2 cups water and chopped green chiles.
Bring to a boil.
Add half the can of tomatoes, smashing the tomatoes with your hand into the pot.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and oregano.

title: carrot and onion casserole
directions: Separate onions into rings and saute a few minutes in butter. Heat cheese spread over boiling water until melted.
Combine cracker crumbs, pepper and thyme.
Layer onions, carrots, cheese and crumbs in greased shallow pan.
Sprinkle with pimento.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and Cool Whip together and fold in fruit, celery and nuts.
Enjoy!

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until browned (drain).
Make 3 layers in crock-pot of above items in order.
Put on low for 5 hours.

title: angel cake
directions: Sift flour with the first 3/4 cup of sugar 2 times; set aside. Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar, vanilla and salt.
Continue beating until stiff enough to form soft peaks but still moist and glossy.
Add remaining 3/4 cup of sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, continuing to beat until egg whites hold stiff peaks.
Sift about 1/4 of the flour mixture over whites; fold in.
Repeat, folding in remaining flour by fourths.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Invert cake in pan.
Cool thoroughly.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine enough apples to fill 10 dumplings.
Stretch each biscuit; fill with apples.
Pinch together and place in greased pan.
Mix butter, sugar and 7-Up.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: game hens
directions: Split hens and brown in large covered skillet with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Sprinkle hens in and out with salt, pepper and flour.
Dissolve bouillon in water and pour over hens.
Reduce heat to simmer, sprinkle with thyme and bay leaves, cover and simmer about 40 minutes or until tender.
(Add wine last 20 minutes, if desired.)

title: party platter crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add soy sauce and garlic and onion salts.
Stir with a wooden spoon. Spread noodles, rice cereal and peanuts on a jelly roll pan. Drizzle with margarine mixture.
Stir to coat.
Bake 5 minutes; stir well.
Bake another 5 minutes, until light brown.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese and toss together.
Pile lightly into baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves eight.
(Sometimes I substitute chopped chicken for the turkey and if it appears too dry I add a little broth.)

title: black devil's food cake
directions: Measure into bowl without sifting flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt. Make 3 holes in dry ingredients. In first hole put vinegar. In second hole put vanilla. In third hole put cooking oil. Over top pour cold water.

title: cookie bars
directions: Line cookie pan with graham crackers.
Boil butter, oleo and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and spread chopped nuts over them.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Lift immediately onto foil.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli on bottom of casserole dish.
Add juices of chicken.
In saucepan, mix all ingredients while heating over low heat.
Pour over chicken.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ronda's texas favorite
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add other ingredients. Wrap in a flour tortilla and serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Place allspice, 1 cinnamon stick and cloves in a cheesecloth. Immerse in cider or apple juice.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with cinnamon stick in each mug.
This is a very warming drink on a cold night.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix box of Swiss chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt the margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Spoon over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Spread in pan and chill about 1 hour. Beat together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and milk.
Spread on crackers.
Top with chopped nuts.
Spread Dream Whip or Cool Whip over nuts.
Top with pie filling mixed with almond flavoring and chill.

title: stuffed steak roll
directions: You will need toothpicks and foil.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla together until thick and lemon in color.
Stir in the grated zucchini.
Add the sifted flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder. Fold in the raisins and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a greased and floured pan.
Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Sprinkle on powdered sugar.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Fill greased muffin pans (12) 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately roll in 1/2 cup melted butter, then a mixture of 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Heat cream and butter until butter melts.
Drain noodles.
Put 1/2 in a bowl.
Add 1/2 cream and noodle mixture and sprinkle cheese.
Toss, then add the rest of the noodles, cream and cheese and toss.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well with spoon. Mixture should be stiff. If not, add a teaspoon of flour and a teaspoon cornmeal until right consistency. Scoop out with tablespoon. Spoon into hot oil. Hush puppies should flip over on their own. When golden brown, remove from oil.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare a day ahead of time.
Layer each ingredient on top of each other in order listed.
Refrigerate and sprinkle bacon bits on top just before serving.

title: savory green beans
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet and add ginger, garlic and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Add the green beans and 1 onion, sliced thin and separated into rings.
Add chicken stock or chicken soup cubes. Add bay leaf and parsley flakes.
Season to taste.
Cook over gentle flame, about 10 minutes, stirring from time to time.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: herb-roasted turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Wash turkey and reserve giblets. Carefully rinse and dry bird inside and out. Rub all surfaces with salt and pepper, including cavity. Place 12 sprigs of thyme in cavity. Put onions, carrots, celery, bay leaves and 6 thyme sprigs and peppercorns on bottom of large roasting pan. Place turkey on top of vegetables. Cover opening of cavity with foil. Pour butter over all surfaces of turkey. Sprinkle on sage, thyme and chives. Cover loosely with tent of aluminum foil. Roast 2 1/2 hours, undisturbed. Remove foil to let skin brown. Baste every 20 minutes for 1 hour. Turkey should cook to an internal temperature of 165°. Remove from oven. Let set 20 to 60 minutes before carving.

title: new orleans red beans
directions: Soak beans in quart of water overnight.
Cook beans.
When half done, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until all ingredients are soft.
Mash 1 cup beans and add to make beans thick.
Serve over rice.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Drain and set aside. Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in mushrooms, olives and tomatoes. Simmer 10 minutes. Spread 1/2 cooked spaghetti into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with 1/2 of the sauce and 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Repeat in layers. Combine soup and water. Mix well. Spread over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except paprika.
Pour into ungreased 7 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika before baking.

title: summer seafood salad
directions: Season with selected portions of whole cumin seed, sweet basil, minced garlic, whole celery seed and dill seed.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: Blend thoroughly on medium speed in blender.
Store in quart jar in the refrigerator.
Good on mixed green salad with Blue cheese crumbled on top.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix Accent, onion, chives and beef.
Add cream cheese and mix thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans until coated.
Serve or refrigerate until later.

title: alpine goulash
directions: Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over hot egg noodles.
Delicious.

title: super simple summer cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package and add the pineapple. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan. When done, poke holes in top of cake and cover with vanilla pudding (made as directed on package). Chill.
When ready to serve, ice with whipped topping.

title: glory fried chops
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops.
Pour off fat. Stir in soup and water. Cover. Cook over low heat for about 45 minutes or until tender. Stir now and then.

title: dried fruit and nut candy
directions: If some fruits are very dry or hard, pour boiling water over them and let them soak about 15 minutes. Drain.
Put dried fruits in food processor and process until mixture is "ground together".

title: grandmother's molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, push to one side of the bowl.
Beat eggs in the other side, blend mixture.
Mix molasses with water. Sift together all dry ingredients, add alternately with liquid, beating only enough to mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: chili
directions: Cook the meat, beef or turkey; drain off any grease. Saute the green peppers, onions and garlic for about 4 to 5 minutes until soft. Mix all the ingredients in a large pot and simmer for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. If it's not hot enough, you can add hot sauce.

title: salmon appetizers
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove any bones that are prevalent.
In a small bowl, combine salmon, cheese, salsa, parsley and cilantro. Add cumin if desired.
Spread 2 tablespoons of mixture over tortilla.
Roll each tortilla up tightly; wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Slice each tortilla into bite size pieces.
Makes pinwheel appetizers.

title: broiled oriental fish
directions: Heat broiler.
Combine oil and next 5 ingredients in a shallow baking dish; stir until blended.
Place fish fillets in marinade. Turn to coat.
Marinate for 20 minutes.
Turn occasionally.
Wash green onions; trim tops so onions are 5 to 6 inches in length. Split bottoms 3 inches to give onions a feathered look.
Place onions in marinade for last 10 minutes.
Remove fish and onions. Place on broiler pan.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Place in oven 4 to 5 inches from heat.
Broil 3 minutes.
Turn fish and onions carefully using a pancake turner and broil 3 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Mix chicken and celery soup with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Put stuffing mix over top.
Melt butter.
Pour 1 3/4 cups chicken broth over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: mike's deep dish brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Spread in a greased 8 inch square pan. Bake at 350° until brownies begin to pull away from edges of pan. Cool and cut in squares.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill. Serve with a variety of fresh vegetables.

title: spiced cranberry-orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O completely in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened just a little.
Stir in oranges and walnuts.
This can be put in a mold if desired.
Refrigerate until firm.
This makes about 10 servings and keeps very well.

title: seattle frozen chocolate frango
directions: Using electric mixer, beat together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add melted chocolate and continue beating thoroughly. Add the whole eggs; beat again until fluffy.
Beat in peppermint and vanilla flavorings.
Sprinkle half the crumbs in each of 18 cupcake pan liners.
Spoon chocolate mixture into liners.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream and cherries.
Makes 18 small, rich servings.

title: quick and easy fruit salad(for my husband, ken, with love)
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit, reserving pineapple juice. Combine juice, pudding mix and instant drink.
Mix; stir well. Combine with fruit; toss gently.
Chill!

title: glaze for baked ham
directions: The last 25 minutes of baking ham, combine ingredients and pour over ham.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour.
Mix.
Pour in loaf pan or tube pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour (until center tests done).

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and juice to a good boil; let stand for 2 minutes.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk; chill for 10 minutes, then gently stir in Cool Whip. Chill until firm.
Can sprinkle nuts on top before serving.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and make 8 patties.
Spray frying pan with Pam and fry crisp.

title: pralines
directions: Lightly coat wax paper with vegetable cooking spray and set aside.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients except pecans and vanilla in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly for 1 to 2 minutes or until a candy thermometer reaches 220°.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Remove from heat and beat with a wooden spoon 4 to 6 minutes or just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tablespoon onto prepared wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Do not double recipe.

title: mildred's casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; drain and place in a casserole dish. Make sauce of cheese and 1 stick margarine by melting together. Pour sauce over broccoli.
Crumble crackers and mix with remaining stick of margarine.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: meat balls and rice
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, eggs, onion, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Make 15 small meat balls.
Combine tomatoes and juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water in a large skillet; bring mixture to boil and add meat balls.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Remove meat balls from liquid.
To thicken liquid for gravy, mix 1 tablespoon flour to 3/4 cup water and pour into tomato mixture. Add meat balls and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Mix milk and water.
Add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Equals 1 can Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend ingredients and roll into long roll. Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in thin wheels and bake.

title: swiss steak and corn pudding
directions: Dust steak with seasoned flour; brown in shortening.
Add onion slices and tomatoes; cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours. Meantime, combine corn, eggs (which have been well beaten), salt, pepper, carrots, onion, crumbs and milk.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serve with hot Borden Bake 'N' Eat biscuits, Pineapple Brown Betty and hot coffee.

title: macaroni and cheese with tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, onion and sugar.
Pour macaroni into baking dish while hot and add a little butter or margarine.
Add tomato mixture and mix.
Add shredded cheese.
Top with pieces of American cheese and cover.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and brown, if desired.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs and butter, in a medium bowl. Pour into a 4-quart casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Put water and sugar in pan on stove; add a pinch of salt and let come to a boil.
Mix cocoa and flour with a little water and then add to boiling sugar water mixture.
Stir until thickens. Serve with hot biscuits.

title: italian lasagne
directions: First mix sausage, hamburger and onion.
Brown and drain. Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add a little water if needed.
Mix in Parmesan cheese.
Layer, starting with meat mixture, then cooked noodles, then cottage cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Put cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350°. Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Press crescent rolls in a pie plate.
Spread mustard onto crust.
Saute zucchini, onion and spices in margarine slightly. Drain most of the liquid.
Mix cheese and eggs together.
Add zucchini mixture. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip in a bread bowl
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and vegetable soup mix until well blended.
Add spinach, water chestnuts and pepper.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place rice in casserole.
Heat soups, butter and salt.
Pour over rice.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread sticks
directions: Roll out biscuits like snakes.
Dip in egg and roll in crushed corn flakes, Rice Krispies or cracker crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses; mix well.
Add other ingredients. Mix. Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn stuffed onions(microwaved)
directions: Hollow out onions; chop centers to make 1 cup.
Fill onions with corn; place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook, covered, at Cycle 1 (High power) for 16 minutes.
Combine butter and chopped onions; cook, uncovered, at Cycle 2 (High power) for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring.
Stir in soup, any remaining corn and cheese. Cook at Cycle 1 (High power) for 1 minute.
Stir once.
Spoon sauce over onions; cook, uncovered, at Cycle 1 (High power) for 6 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Pour water mix over flour. Put eggs, soda and vanilla into buttermilk.
Mix with fork, then pour over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Frost when hot.

title: fresh basil and tomato sauce
directions: In large
saucepan,
heat olive oil; add chopped basil, tomatoes and garlic;
cook	over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.	Season	with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat when slightly	thickened
and	pour
over pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Bring butter, sugar, milk and cocoa to boil point.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour into a greased dish.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix the vegetables, pimentos and salt together. Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Drain and rinse in cold water. Drain well again. Mix the remaining ingredients in a dishpan and bring to a boil. Add cucumber mixture and bring to a boil. Simmer for 20 minutes. Put in pint jars and seal. Makes 7 or 8 pints.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix cheese, sugar and eggs well.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, and pour into 13 by 9 greased pan.
Carefully spoon ricotta mixture to cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 65 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.	Sprinkle with powder sugar.

title: tiramisu dessert(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. In a large bowl, whisk together the mascarpone, sugar and amaretto until smooth.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and celery; drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Mix butter, sour cream, eggs, vanilla, dry yeast and water in a mixer. Add flour and salt. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Divide dough in 4 pieces. Mix 1 cup of sugar with 1 tablespoon vanilla and use to roll out dough. Sprinkle a board with sugar and vanilla mixture; roll dough into a rectangle and sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Fold dough into thirds; cut and twist into bow tie shapes. Let sit on ungreased cookie sheets for 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes (use high rack in oven). Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: chicken creole casserole
directions: Cook chicken saving 1 quart of broth.
To the broth add the onion, celery, green pepper, and spaghetti.
Cook until tender. Add the cheese, sauce, mushrooms, and pimentos.
Stir until melted. Add chicken chunks.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.
Can be made before and refrigerated or frozen.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Dissolve flour in water.
Cook everything together for 15 minutes after it comes to a boil. Pour into jars and seal. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: oven pork chop and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Combine soup, onion mix and rice.
Stir in water.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chops on top and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: cheesy onion muffins
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, flour, Parmesan cheese, dried onion and parsley.
Beat egg white with milk and stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fill muffin cups half full (should have been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray first).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
You should be able to stick a toothpick in the center and have it come out clean. Makes 12 muffins.

title: strawberry marshmallow delight
directions: Pour 2/3 cup of evaporated milk in a refrigerator ice tray. Place in freezer until ice crystals begin to form around the edges.
In a quart saucepan, combine marshmallows and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until marshmallows are just melted.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, lemon rind and water.
Chill until slightly thicker than unbeaten egg whites.
Place cold milk in quart bowl; whip with cold rotary beater or with electric mixer at high speed until stiff.
Fold into marshmallow mixture.
Fold in strawberries and pour into chilled pie crust.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours).

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix gelatin and 1/4 cup cold water together to soften gelatin. Heat tomato soup and mix with cream cheese to blend well. Cool. Add rest together and put in mold.
Use Sociables crackers or others.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Grease	pie
plate,
x 1 1/2-inch, or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Cook and stir the ground beef and onion in 10-inch
skillet
until
beef
is
brown;
drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spoon into pie plate.

title: spam-hominy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole, beat eggs lightly; add milk, then hominy, Spam, corn meal, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: chili john's chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; add rest of the ingredients except beans.
Stir after adding.
Simmer for at least 2 hours. Add beans, simmer 5 more minutes.
Let sit 1/2 hour.

title: almond jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining water and milk.
Add almond extract and chill until set.
Serve with fresh fruit salad on top.

title: "hominy casserole"
directions: Stir and put in a casserole dish.
Put corn chips on top and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: rice krispies coconut cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls and flatten.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease baking dish with oleo. Pat rice in bottom of pan. Place cut up chicken on rice and pour milk, mushroom soup, salt and pepper over chicken. Bake in 300° oven until chicken is golden brown.

title: frozen orange jello salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple with juice; let come to a "good" boil.
Cool.
Put in refrigerator and let begin to congeal.
Be sure it is not completely congealed.
Remove when it begins to harden and add 2 cups of buttermilk and 2 cups of Cool Whip. Freeze.
Keeps well when thawed for a reasonable time; remains firm.
Freeze for at least 3 hours before using.

title: orange cream cheese muffins
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg and juice; beat well. Stir in Bisquick until moistened.
Grease Texas muffin pans well. Put 1/4 cup batter into each one.
Spoon 1 teaspoon marmalade in each.
Top each with remaining batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes on rack before removing.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate until firm.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Putting lettuce on bottom, layer ingredients.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add black pepper, red pepper, chili powder and garlic salt.
Drain grease; set aside. Melt cheese in Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add ground beef.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Combine onion, tomatoes and lettuce in large salad bowl.
Pour ground beef mixture over salad.
Add dip size Fritos. Toss and serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip drops
directions: Blend shortening and peanut butter.
Cream with sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in rolled oats, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Open rolls and place a spoon of chicken and a slice of cheese in each roll.
Roll up as you would for baking.
Mix soup and milk.
Place rolls in casserole dish and pour soup mixture over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix well the sugar, milk, butter and salt. Add the coconut and nuts. Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and allow to cool on waxed paper. Refrigerate.
These freeze well.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Arrange cherries in greased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over cherries.
Bake in 370° oven 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: mama's fudge
directions: Bring to a boil, sugar, milk and chocolate.
Turn down to medium and boil for 7 minutes.
Take off heat and add pecans, butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into well buttered plate, hot!
Let set and serve.

title: hominy
directions: In a large skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute onion and garlic until tender. Add the drained hominy, tomatoes, chilies, chili powder, cumin and pepper; mix gently. Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: alabama camp stew
directions: Cook the heck out of the meat!
Skim off fat; tear meat from bones.
Simmer raw vegetables in broth and shredded meat with seasonings.
When vegetables are tender, add canned vegetables and simmer until all flavors are inner mixed.
One-fourth cup sugar is optional;
I use 1/4 cup.
Cook meat the day before you serve it.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and mix.
Just before serving, add one bag of taco chips.

title: fresh strawberry butter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Store in refrigerator. Delicious on pound cake, toast or ice cream.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In electric skillet combine sugar, butter and milk and set heat control at 280°.
Bring mixture to rolling boil; boil 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn heat off.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and blended.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds of candy.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix water, sugar and Kool-Aid together. Chill. When punch is ready to be served, add chilled pineapple juice and Sprite to Kool-Aid mixture.
Stir and serve.
Sherbet can be added if desired.
Will provide 25 (6 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Beat eggs; add milk and then dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat whites of 2 eggs until stiff or peak is formed.
Add 4 tbsp of sugar and mix well.
Put on pie and bake in oven until light brown.

title: microwaved vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions.
Leave whole.
Core a hole in top of onion.
Salt and pepper the onion.
Spread a pat of margarine into the hole. Push one beef cube down into margarine.
Cover with plastic wrap. Cook until tender in microwave.

title: herb mixes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a jar, seal tightly. Store in a cool, dark place.
This mix is suitable for a variety of Italian recipes, from risotto to spaghetti sauce.
Season dishes to taste.

title: mostaccioli casserole(serves 8)
directions: Cook 1/2 pound of mostaccioli noodles.
Saute green pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and slices of American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate velvet cake
directions: Melt semisweet chocolate morsels in microwave safe bowl at HIGH for 30 second intervals until melted (about 1-1/2 minutes total time).
Stir until smooth.
Beat butter and brown sugar at medium speed with a electric mixer, about 5 minutes, until well blended.
Add egg, 1 at a time, beating until just until blended. Add melted chocolate, beating just until blended.
Sift together flour, baking soda, and salt.
Gradually add to chocolate mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Gradually add 1 cup hot water in a slow steady stream, beating at low speed just until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter evenly into 9-inch cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes then remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks before frosting.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Cover with American cheese.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Gradually add milk to Bisquick; mix to consistency of biscuit dough.
Turn onto a floured board and knead until easily handled. Roll dough very thin.
Let dry for 1 hour; cut into strips and drop into boiling broth.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili chicken
directions: With a fork, beat egg and milk.
In a bowl, mix together flour, seasoning mix and flavor enhancer.
Dip chicken in egg, then in flour mixture.

title: italian soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: faith recipe
directions: Take faith and spread generously through each day God has given you. Add hope to every good deed.

Thank God for giving you graces you need. Take charity and sift all around to family, friends and anyone you can find. Bake for a lifetime and ice it generously with love. You will have a heavenly recipe.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, spices, salt and soda.
Mix together oil, raisins, nuts and pumpkin.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar replacement.
Add eggs, beating well.
Beat in cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in sifter and beat into creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir in sour cream, raisins and walnuts.

title: peachy bran muffins
directions: Combine yogurt and cereal.
Mix lightly. Add raisins, carrot, sugar, oil and egg whites.
Mix well. Combine flour and cinnamon and add to cereal mixture. Stir just until moistened. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chelela's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pearls 'n chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, Nestle cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle Toll House Treasures Premier White deluxe baking pieces.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes, until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand two minutes before removing from cookie sheets; cool completely.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda together.
Add to other ingredients; drop by spoon on a greased cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Then add flour.
Add egg yolks, then add the juice and rind of 1 lemon.
Add milk and egg whites (beaten until stiff) last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake 35 minutes in slow oven for 10 minutes at 400°, then decreased to 350° for the remaining 25 minutes.

title: bailey's pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: In a bowl, cream the softened cream cheese and add drained pineapple and Bailey's.
Mix well.
Divide in half and form two balls.
Put nuts in a bowl and roll each cheese ball in nuts until covered.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar; work in the butter as for pastry.
Add milk; roll out in sheets.
Mark in strips 1-inch wide and prick with fork 1-inch apart.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Punch holes 1-inch apart all over top of cake.
Combine pineapple and sugar; microwave 1 minute and pour over cake.
Mix instant pudding according to directions.
Pour over top of cake.
Slice bananas; place on top of pudding.
Spread layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours. Slice and serve.

title: carrot salad with fruit
directions: In medium bowl, toss together.
Cover in refrigerator until well chilled.
Serves 4.

title: hash brown dish
directions: Layer hash brown patties in bottom of deep dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together; spread on top of hash browns.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and gradually add sugars, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs, then mix with brown sugar.
Add flour, then margarine.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in greased pan (9 x 13-inch) at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: no fuss pork chops
directions: In a skillet, cook pork chops in oil until brown on both sides, about 8 minutes. Add onions; cook until tender. Combine pineapple juice, brown sugar and vinegar; pour over chops. Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 15 minutes.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: In a skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp and saute onion.
Drain on paper towel.
Add cabbage to bacon drippings.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring often. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes more.
Stir in bacon, vinegar, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Fold in chopped apple and currant jelly.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes more, or until cabbage is tender, but crisp.
Serves 6.

title: bubbles
directions: Gently mix all ingredients in a bowl.

title: double pie crust
directions: Mix and roll out 2 pie crusts.

title: microwave easy gravy
directions: Pour drippings into 4 cup glass measure.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Pour in liquid and stir briskly until well blended.
Cook on High (maximum power) 3 to 4 minutes or until boiling, stirring several times during cooking.
Season with salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Serve hot with meat, potatoes or dressing.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Grease Bundt pan well.
Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Will make approximately 2 layers.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of rolls.
Sprinkle pudding mix over brown sugar.
Add cinnamon.
Cut margarine in small pieces and place evenly on top of other ingredients.
Cover with wax paper.
Let sit on kitchen counter overnight.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in a large bowl all of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Store in containers in refrigerator.

title: one-two-three
directions: Mix together.
Roll on floured surface.
Now let your imagination take over.
Use cookie cutters or whatever.
These are excellent for canapes or snacks.
Once again, depending on what you plan to use them for, sprinkle cheese, nuts, confectioners sugar or whatever.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato puffs
directions: Preheat deep fryer oil to 385°.
Combine all ingredients and drop mixture into oil by tablespoonfuls.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: squash minestra
directions: In
large
saucepan,
heat oil and saute onion until it becomes
transparent, but not brown.
Add celery and zucchini; saute
for
a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Fill
pot
with
water, about 3 inches above all vegetables and cook for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and bouillon cubes;
cook
on low heat until potatoes are tender.
This can be served
with
cooked pasta (tobetti).
Cook pasta according to package
directions.
Drain
pasta
and
mix
together with vegetable mixture.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: six week bran muffin mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine and buttermilk. Store in a tight container in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 6 weeks for use as desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kitchen brew
directions: Mix all together in saucepan and let simmer on back of stove for a wonderful, homey fragrance.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together powdered sugar, margarine and cream cheese. In another bowl mix pudding with milk until smooth, then blend with cream cheese mixture and fold in whipped topping.
In a container, layer cookies first; then add a layer of cream mixture. Continue layering, ending with a cookie layer.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Fill center of each noodle and roll up.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place rolls (seam down) in dish.
Cover with sauce and bake for 20 minutes at 325°, covered.
Remove cover and bake an additional five minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese (extra) and broil for 1 minute. Makes 6 servings.

title: old-timey tea cakes
directions: Measure out 4 cups of flour.
Add gradually to other ingredients, until mixed.
Do not make too dry.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine half the strawberries, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and food coloring. Cook and stir until clear. Cool and add other half of strawberries. Pour into baked cooled pie shell. Refrigerate and top if desired before serving.

title: chocolate topping
directions: In a double boiler, mix cream and egg.
Add sugar and chocolate (cut up fine).
Cook over simmering water until thick. Serve on vanilla ice cream.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix first
7 ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well and add pears and nuts.
Bake in well-greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed coffee cake(very easy!  very good!)
directions: Combine poppy seed and buttermilk; soak overnight in refrigerator.
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add vanilla to buttermilk mixture.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture alternately to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Spoon half the batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: fruit mix
directions: Mix fruit (except strawberries) in a large bowl. Mix Tang and pudding mix. Add to fruit mixture. Add strawberries last. Mix well.

title: salt and pepper-crusted pork
directions: Combine pepper, salt, rosemary and garlic in small bowl.

Rub over pork. Let pork stand at least 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°. Heat oil in heavy medium ovenproof skillet over high heat. Add pork and brown on all sides, about 6 minutes. Transfer skillet with pork to oven and roast pork until pork is cooked through, turning occasionally, about 20 minutes. Slice and serve. Makes 2 servings. Can be doubled or tripled.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Pour lemon juice over shrimp and chop.
Mix shrimp and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Best if made day before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whisk pudding and milk together until thick.
Beat whipping cream until thick (with electric mixer).
Fold whipped cream into pudding mixture with whisk or rubber spatula.
Great with fresh strawberries.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Thaw and chop frozen spinach or cook and chop fresh spinach. Drain well and set aside.
Mix well Ricotta, egg, oregano, salt, pepper and only 1 cup Mozzarella.
Stir spinach into the cheese mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and put in 1/3 of the sauce. Next, layer 3 uncooked noodles, then 1/2 of the cheese mixture. Repeat one time.
Put last of noodles on top and cover with the last 1/3 of sauce.
Top with the remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella. Pour 1 1/4 cups water all around the edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: hot holiday cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos as small as possible and mix with butter.
Layer in pan.
Fix pudding as directed on box, then mix with cream cheese.
Layer on top of crushed Oreos.
Layer Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Finally, sprinkle crushed cookies on top.
Refrigerate for one hour, then serve.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(sugar-free)
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth for 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into greased 9 x 1 1/4-inch or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
In a glass pie plate, bake at 325° to 350°.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.

title: kay's spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs and milk with fork.
Pour evenly over cooked spaghetti.
Cover with spaghetti sauce, then pepperoni and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Break chunk ham into small pieces. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake in a lightly greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with buttered bread crumbs if desired.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: emparados
directions: Brown hamburger with the next 3 ingredients.
After browned, add next 7 ingredients.
Cook on low until ready to fill pastry.

title: banana cake
directions: Stir flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
In separate bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add bananas.
Add sour milk alternately with flour mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 25 minutes.
This cake is good topped with cream cheese frosting and sprinkled with chopped pecans.

title: garlic chive chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chives and garlic; saute briefly.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper generously. Pour chive mixture over it and bake as usual.

title: noodles and beef
directions: Boil beef in beef broth.
When tender, add noodles.
Cook until tender.
Serve.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually add powdered sugar and cream well. Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in salt and flour.
Chill. Roll out half of dough at a time, cut into diamond shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 325° for 12 to 16 minutes.

title: depression cake
directions: In a cup melt shortening the size of a walnut.
Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Fill cup with milk.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Combine 1/4 cup brown sugar, 2 teaspoons orange juice and 2 teaspoons melted margarine.
Mix and set aside for glaze.
Whip potatoes until smooth; beat in eggs.
Add sugar, orange juice and melted butter.
Add salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix; pour in casserole.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Pour glaze topping over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with orange slices and marshmallows.
Put under broiler until brown.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin lemon slices; squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon.
Set aside.

title: chocolate crunch pretzels
directions: Crush cereal between two sheets of wax paper with rolling pin. Mix crushed cereal and mini chocolate chips together, then spread this mixture onto a serving tray.
With a butter knife, spread a coat of peanut butter on approximately half of the pretzel rod. Then roll the coated part of rod in cereal and chip mixture. Repeat for all pretzel rods.
Great snack for 6 to 8 kids.

title: welsh-style eggs
directions: Butter 6 ovenproof dishes lavishly.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the grated cheese in the bottom of each buttered dish.
Break the eggs in a saucer and then slip the eggs (2) over the surface of the cheese.
Take care not to break yolk.
Allow 2 eggs per dish. Sprinkle the remainder of the cheese over the surface of each dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Beat low speed until crumbly. Press in bottom of oiled pan. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla. Pour over crumb mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: new year's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients into blender and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: juicy burgers
directions: Add all ingredients and cook over low heat for 30 minutes. Spoon over bread slices.
Serve with cole slaw and potato chips.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Stir all together until smooth.
Pour in cake pan and bake at 350°.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix jello and hot water; let set for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients; chill overnight.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Boil beef, tomatoes and rice together until beef changes color.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Cook in covered casserole in oven at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: rosa's chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding only enough mayonnaise to make creamy.
Allow salad to rest overnight in refrigerator to allow ingredients to mix.
Makes great sandwiches or stuffing in half a cantaloupe for a summers lunch.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Season tomatoes with salt, sugar and pepper.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 13 x 9-inch pan.
After baking, poke holes in cake with the back of wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and caramel topping over cake.
Smooth Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle candy bar over top.
Refrigerate.

title: quickie dillie bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; add all other ingredients except flour and mix well.
Gradually add flour and beat until smooth and elastic.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Place in greased casserole 2-quart size and let rise uncovered until light to touch, about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; brush with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and cover with damp cloth for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350°
about 45 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Combine
juice	from cherries and pineapple, add enough water to equal
2 cups.
Bring to boil, pour jello in and stir until dissolved.	When
cool,
add
Coca-Cola
and chill until partly set.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into mold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white trash
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients.
Pour over remainder of ingredients.
Put mix in plastic bag and coat with 1 1/2 boxes powdered sugar.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain and simmer with tomatoes, tomato paste and spices.
Stir often.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Boil lasagne noodles according to package directions until soft.
Drain and add olive oil to keep noodles from sticking.
Grease a large casserole dish and arrange a layer of noodles on the bottom, then a layer of sauce, cottage cheese (all), more noodles and more sauce.
Layer noodles and sauce until gone and top with cheese. Bake until brown on top.

title: yogurt cream pie
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip.
Add fruit and mix gently.
Spoon into crust and freeze for 4 hours.
Place in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.

title: tabouli(armenian salad)
directions: Pour boiling water over bulgar wheat in a deep bowl. Cover and let sit 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.
Mix in all ingredients.
Let sit in the refrigerator overnight.

title: sea breeze salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add nuts, pineapple and milk.
Refrigerate until set.

title: hawaiian pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix well in an electric mixer and pour in an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm, about 1 hour.

title: bacon and cheese chicken
directions: Cover chicken fillets with the Shake 'n Bake mix.
Wrap each fillet with bacon strips.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Melt cheese on top for 5 minutes.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Cut cake into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place 1/2 of cubes in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 cup cherry pie filling for top; spoon remainder over cake in pan.
Add rest of cake.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake. Chill at least 5 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares for serving.
Garnish with reserved cherries.
Serves 8.

title: taco spread appetizer
directions: Mix together the sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Spread evenly in a 9 x 9-inch square Tupperware pan.
Shortly before serving, chop some iceberg lettuce into small pieces and spread over top.
Chop green pepper, tomato and onion very fine. Sprinkle evenly over the lettuce.
Serve with assorted crackers and tortilla chips.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown meat and onion in 3-pound coffee can or large camp pot over hot coals.
Add broth and vegetables.
Cover and let simmer 1 hour.
Give everyone a spoon and bowl and enjoy!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large kettle, bring all ingredients to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaves.
Freeze or can.

title: quick breadsticks
directions: Add water to yeast.
Add margarine, salt, flour and sugar. Knead well, adding more flour, if necessary.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Break off pieces and roll into breadstick shape.
Sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired, and salt.
Bake at 550°, about 6 minutes, on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with melted margarine, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and mix well with other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple and liquid to simmer.
Remove from heat, add jello and set aside to cool.
After cooled, add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Put in container and refrigerate.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Pare and grate potatoes or put through a food chopper.
Add the sugar and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat in the egg and add the butter and nutmeg.
Turn into a well-greased shallow pudding pan and bake until brown in a 350° oven.
If desired, the top may then be spread with 1 cup of preserves and a meringue.
Brown in a 300° oven and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and add oil.
Add flour slowly with sugar and cinnamon.
Add carrots and nuts.
Put into 3 round cake pans, buttered and floured.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes to 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Drain fruit.
To juice, add 3 to 4 tablespoons of cornstarch and sugar and cook until thick.
Cool and add fruit.
Pour in baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add walnuts and raisins.
Cream together brown sugar and butter.
Add apples and cold coffee. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Turn into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish in large pan.
Salt.
Mix dressing ingredients. Stuff in fish cavity.
Place 4 strips of bacon over fish.
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours or until fish is done and brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix filling and crushed pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Dribble margarine over it.
Add nuts and/or coconut.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown sausage.
Save 2 tablespoons drippings to saute onions, celery and pepper.
Add to beans and meat, then also add tomato juice, sugar, salt, chili powder and cayenne.
Mix well and simmer (lid off) until it becomes a little thick or cook in crock-pot. Serve with Italian bread or corn bread.

title: chicken-apple salad
directions: Combine chicken, apples, celery and almonds in large bowl. Mix mayonnaise, honey, lemon juice and salt together and add chicken mixture.
Toss well and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add peanut butter and milk. Beat until mixed well. Fold in topping. Spoon into crust.
Garnish with chocolate.
Refrigerate.

title: seven layer salad #2
directions: Into 13 x 9 inch pan (or use large clear glass salad bowl) put layer of lettuce, onions, celery, green pepper. Add the cooked, drained and cooled green peas. Pour the mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle sugar on top, then add cheddar cheese and top with bacon. Refrigerate overnight or all day for maximum flavor.

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, put over heat and let come to a boil.
Stir in soda.
Continue to boil until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Beat until creamy; add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Continue beating until rather thick. When cooled, pour into buttered dish and cut into squares.

title: cranbrosia salad
directions: Spray molds with Pam.
Combine cranberries and sugar and mix to dissolve sugar.
Sprinkle gelatin over pineapple juice in saucepan over medium heat and stir constantly until dissolved. Add to cranberry mixture and stir.
Stir in fruits.
Fold in sour cream and whipped cream. Chill in mold or bowl until firm.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add onion, ground beef, egg, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix.
Form in small balls and saute in butter or oleo until slightly brown.
Add bouillon and mushroom soup; simmer 15 minutes.
Cook large package noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Fold into meatball mixture and serve.

title: brownie swirl cheesecake
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions on package.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, sour cream and pepper.
Pour into quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with French fried onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: onion soup casserole(original recipe)
directions: Saute onions in small amount of margarine.
Add onion soup, bay leaf, bouillon, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a rolling boil and add cheese.
Simmer 1/2 hour, then thicken with cornstarch and cold water.
Pour into a long glass baking dish. Lay sliced Italian bread on top.
Add slices of Provolone cheese and toast under the broiler.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Use crisp, fresh vegetables.
Very good.

title: spinach and orzo pie
directions: In a medium bowl combine eggs, the cooked orzo, 1/2 cup of the spaghetti sauce, and parmesan cheese. Spread mixture over the bottom and up sides of a greased 9 inch pie plate to form a shell. Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. In another bowl stir together spinach, ricotta cheese, and nutmeg. Spoon into bottom of pasta lined pie plate. Spread remaining spaghetti sauce atop filling. Cover edge of pie with foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Top with shredded cheese. Return to oven and bake for 3 to 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted. Transfer to a wire rack; let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: frozen hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and onions in a 12 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, 1/4 c. melted butter, soup, and cheese in a medium bowl, stir well.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes and stir lightly.
Combine cornflakes and melted butter, sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield 12 servings.

title: carrot and mushroom saute
directions: Place carrots in pan.
Add boiling water to cover by 1 inch. Boil, partially covered, until tender-crisp, 5 to 8 minutes. Drain.

title: tollerini
directions: Cook all together 10 minutes.
Pour in greased casserole. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pan-fried chicken strips
directions: Heat a large frying pan.
Add oil, chicken, garlic and green onions. Saute over high heat until chicken is lightly browned and tender.
Remove from pan.
Add Marsala and lemon juice.
Allow liquid to reduce for a moment. Return chicken to the hot pan, salt and pepper to taste. Do not overcook.
Serve immediately.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine and set aside.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Pour on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lois' salad
directions: Heat applesauce until bubbly hot.
Add jello and dissolve well.
Add 7-Up slowly and stir until well mixed.
You may have to re-stir a few times until foam goes down.
Chill until set.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: sugar cookies(emily elizabeth's cookie recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla. In seperate bowl combine flour and salt, the mix with butter, egg, sugar mixture. Chill dough for at least 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 350° On floured surface, roll out dough to 1\8 inch thickness and cut into shapes, with floured cookie cutters. Bake on a greased cookie sheet for about 8 min.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients. Stir together and chill.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; set 1/2 cup crumbs aside.
Mix melted butter with rest of crumbs and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crumbs; freeze.
When ice cream is frozen, spread chocolate fudge on top and then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cookie crumbs over Cool Whip. Freeze until serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: chicken pot roast
directions: Rub chicken pieces with salt and the soy sauce.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken well on all sides. Combine ginger and sherry; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Transfer chicken to serving dish and keep warm.
Leave mushrooms in skillet; add vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Cook until sauce thickens, stirring occasionally.
Pour over chicken and score.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and bake pie 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Garnish as desired.

title: lamb-vegetable casserole(serves 4)
directions: Wash and cut zucchini into crosswise pieces.
Drain corn. Melt shortening in skillet; brown lamb chops in hot fat on both sides.
Put corn and zucchini in bottom of lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and savory.
Put chops on top of vegetables.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Contains about 299 calories per serving.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: In margarine or butter, saute chopped onion and celery.
Then add bell pepper.
Add drained peas, asparagus and pimiento.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Use juice from water chestnuts to rinse out soup can and add to mix.
Add water chestnuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bayou blend (seafood casserole)
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper,
celery and garlic in 1 stick oleo. In large mixing bowl add
2 cups of cooked regular rice and the sauteed vegetables.
Add mushroom soup, grated cheese, crab meat and the
chopped
shrimp.
Mix
until
well blended. Spray a 9 x 11-inch pan
or
preferably
glass
dish with Pam. Pour in crab and shrimp
mixture.
Top
with
regular size Ritz crackers. Dot with 1 stick
of
oleo.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Will serve 12.

title: green pepper and pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello and water together until well dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in container.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add more onion and broth, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
