directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Pan-fry slowly, until almost cooked.
Add onions until done.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and paprika.
Pour in vinegar and water.
Cook until thick, then add potatoes.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and Crisco; cool.
Add the sugar and egg.
Sift and add the flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar. Add the chopped walnuts.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: plant food formula
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a gallon of tepid water.
Use only once a week.

title: mexican style manicotti(microwave)
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole crumble ground beef.
Cook, covered, at 100% power for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until no pink remains.
Drain fat.
Stir in refried beans, the first 1/4 cup sliced green onions and cumin.
Spoon meat mixture into cooked manicotti shells.
Arrange the stuffed shells in a 2-quart square microwave-safe casserole dish.
Pour corn and enchilada sauce over shells.
Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap; turn back one corner to vent.
Cook the stuffed shells on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture is heated through, turn dish a half turn once.
Spoon sour cream over casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup green onions, ripe olives and chopped tomato.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: sopapillas
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into bowl; beat together egg, vegetable oil and water.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until well blended.
On a slightly floured cloth or board, knead dough until smooth.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out each piece of dough to a 12-inch size.
Cut into squares.
Put 2 inches of oil in a straight sided pot.
Heat to 380°; fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Keep oil on a constant temperature.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: easy marshmallow four layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and water until blended.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, candies and nuts over crust. Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: microwave rhubarb dessert squares
directions: Blend 2 cups flour, confectioners sugar and butter in large mixing bowl.
Beat until fine crumbs.
Pat 2 cups crumb mixture firmly against bottom of 2-quart dish.
Cook on Level 7 for 4 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes.
Turn dish halfway through cooking time.
Combine eggs, sugar, rhubarb and 1/4 cup flour in 2-quart casserole.
Blend well.
Cook on Full power for 8 to 11 minutes; stir frequently during cooking time.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over rhubarb mixture.
Heat on Full power for 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and top with ice cream or cream.

title: war cake
directions: Put sugar, raisins, water, shortening, cinnamon, cloves and salt in a sauce pan. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Cool. Add baking soda and flour. Mix well. Place in 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: roast beef
directions: *Enough of these for your family.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Mix in order and bake at 325° for 10 minutes, until light brown.

title: baked chicken
directions: Garnish chicken with onion and butter.
Wrap in foil to cover. Bake at 400° for 2 hours.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and cook.
Then pour over carrots in a casserole.
Top with 3 cups buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be microwaved; cook until hot.

title: peach pie
directions: Place drained peach halves in pastry shell, cut sides up.
Mix all ingredients to crumble consistency.
Spoon on top of peaches 30 minutes at 375°.
Reach in oven.
Break up crust on top.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix minced garlic with beef, eggs, chili sauce, parsley, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Make 75 to 85 meatballs.

title: pork oven bake
directions: Pan-fry meat until brown.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with vegetables.
Place kraut on top.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy lemon chicken
directions: Spray a cool grill with all-natural Pam to ensure chicken doesn't stick to grill.
Combine sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, salt and pepper to make sauce; set aside.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Place in a larger baking pan and fill pan with water after placing in oven.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle 1/4 sugar mixture over peaches in pie shell.
Add cream; dot with butter.
Sprinkle rest of mixture on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: the baked apple
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon as much of the mixture into the cored apples.
Drizzle 1 1/2 tablespoons of orange juice concentrate into each apple.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat egg whites first and set aside.
Put all together in bowl and beat until smooth.
Add egg whites and mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Combine next seven ingredients and pour broth over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over mixture and pour broth over crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be made a day ahead or frozen before baking.

title: all beef bake sausage
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape with hands into 3 rolls.
Place each roll on a sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil, shiny side out.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: liz's brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup butter and chocolate squares in saucepan.
Add to same pan the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into greased pan (12 x 12-inch).
Bake slowly for 1 hour at 300°.
Cut while hot.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit or pretzel sticks. Contains approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream until slightly thick.
Add cream cheese.
Whip until thick.
Pour over rest of fruit and fold slightly.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Drain garbanzo beans, reserving juice.
In a blender or food processor fitted with a steel blade, combine beans, lemon juice, tahini, garlic, cumin, green onion, salt and pepper.
Process until smooth.
If mixture is too stiff, add 1 to 2 tablespoons reserved bean juice.
Place bean spread in a medium bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Place on serving plate.
Using a spatula, form chilled spread into a pyramid shape.
Sprinkle with cilantro or parsley.
Garnish with pomegranate seed or olives.
Serve with lavosh or pita bread.
Makes 2 cups.

title: prosciutto chicken rolls
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: easy rice pudding(good hot or cold.)
directions: In a 4-cup glass measuring cup or casserole, combine all ingredients.
Cook on Medium-high (power level 7), covered, 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring occasionally, during the last half of cooking time.
Let stand without cover 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce, butter and soda together.
Mix dry ingredients together; combine and stir thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: shelly peanut butter rice snacks
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine corn syrup and both sugars; cook over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil. Stir in peanut butter.
Add Chex crumbs and put in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and mix lightly.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with cream or a sauce.

title: easy chicken breasts ala orange
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt.
Brown in butter in large skillet.
Remove breasts from skillet and add flour, spices and sugar to drippings.
Stir to a smooth paste.
Gradually add orange juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and smooth.
Reduce heat and add chicken.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving plate and garnish with orange slices and parsley.
Serve with hot rice.
Serve extra sauce separately.
Serves 6.

title: thick and chewy chocolate bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and
vanilla.
Add	combined
flour
and soda;
mix well. Stir in oats,
chocolate
pieces
and nuts.
Spread into well greased 13 x 9-inch
baking
pan.
Bake
at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherry filling into 13 x 9-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Layer crushed pineapple on top.
Sprinkle cake mix on top. Add or top with pats of margarine.
Sprinkle top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes, test with toothpick or sharp knife to be sure batter is done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Cook rice in 1 cup salted boiling water. (Place frozen broccoli on top of rice to thaw.) Cover.
Place broccoli, onion, butter and rice in a baking dish.
Combine soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over the rice-broccoli mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven until bubbly and brown.
This can be prepared before and baked the next day.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix a dash of garlic salt, 1 tablespoon of olive oil and hamburger meat in a saucepan until brown.
Then add onion mix, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and 3 cups water.
Mix together well on high; bring to a boil on high and then turn to low.
Cook for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, cook noodles for 5 to 7 minutes.
Clean noodles real good.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill about 2 hours.
Serve with cucumber slices, carrot sticks, celery, cauliflower, broccoli, etc.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll into a ball.
Then roll in chopped pecans. Chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut up and put into baking dish.
Stir in broth and soup.
Make crust of remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower, stem-side down, on serving plate.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 7 to 11 minutes or until tender, rotating plate twice.
Set aside.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute garlic
in
olive
oil;
add
onions, cabbage and carrots.
Cook
until vegetables are soft.
Stir in meat.
Mix the 2
tablespoons
soy
sauce and the 1 tablespoon cornstarch together and add to the meat mixture.
Cook one minute. Remove from heat and let cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs with sugar, one at a time.
Add milk, margarine, bread and vanilla.
Pour into a pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sweet potato praline
directions: Mix together sweet potato, sugar, melted margarine, vanilla, eggs, milk and salt.
Put in a 9 inch x 13 inch dish.
Mix together brown sugar, flour, cold margarine, and pecan pieces by hand.
Scatter over sweet potato dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oriental pork roast
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork in Brown-in-Bag.
Place in a large baking dish. Trim excess fat from pork.
Place in bag. Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350° for 5 pound roast.

title: oven rice dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ovenproof casserole dish. Cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mash cheese and make smooth by adding milk and mayonnaise. Add seasonings.
Serve with waffle potato chips or corn chips. This will serve crowd of 45.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cover chicken with salted water, to which 2 garlic pods and celery leafs have been added. Cook until meat forks off bones. Let cook completely. Strain off stock. Pick meat off bones and set aside. Reserve 2/3 cup of stock. Bring remainder of stock to boil, add spaghetti and cook according to directions. Make a sauce using reserved 2/3 cup of stock, the oil, chopped onions, 2 pods of garlic, bell pepper, diced celery, tomatoes, and mushrooms. Cook until somewhat thickened. Add diced chicken. Cook and drain spaghetti. Place in large casserole dish. Cover and let sit overnight in refrigerator. Just before baking in 375° oven, cover with grated sharp cheese. Bake 45 minutes covered with foil, then a few minutes without foil.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Finish cooking at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Finely chop half of mushrooms.
Slice remaining mushrooms. Melt butter in large kettle or Dutch oven; saute mushrooms and onion over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in flour; gradually stir in broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Stir in half and half, dry sherry, nutmeg and pepper; heat through. Garnish with croutons.
Makes 6 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery
and
onions
in butter.
Mix rice, soups, Cheez Whiz and
broccoli.
Mix all together and bake in casserole dish at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut into small pieces and place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Pour melted butter evenly over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: empanadas argentinas
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in oil; add ground meat and salt. Fry in large skillet, stirring frequently, until meat is done. Add olives, eggs and raisins.
You can add other seasonings such as nutmeg, paprika, garlic salt and 3 to 4 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Set meat mixture on very low heat so spices can penetrate meat thoroughly.

title: hot rice salad
directions: Place rice, water, salt and yeast flakes in flat baking dish. Cover with
wax
paper
and
foil.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour. Remove
from
oven
and top with remaining ingredients. Garnish with toasted sesame or sunflower seeds and GARLIC HERB DRESSING. Serves 6 to 8.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown venison in frying pan.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir just enough to mix pieces; cover and cook on high for 4 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts by boiling.
Remove bones.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to chicken pieces. Bake in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and slivered almonds (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° for 30 more minutes.

title: cheese tacos
directions: Roll grated cheese and onion into tortillas, softened in hot grease.
Place tacos in greased oblong pan.
Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce lined salad bowl.

title: easy corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on High for 15 minutes or until thickened.

title: bacardi rum cake(now made with regular or pudding cake mix.)
directions: Melt butter. Stir in water and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in rum and add 1/2 cup pecans.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice 1 gallon of cucumbers.
Mix with salt.
Cover with ice for 2 1/2 hours.
Drain, but don't wash.
Slice onions.
Mix onions and cucumbers together.
Put onions and cucumbers in jars. Mix sugar, vinegar, pepper, ginger, celery seed and mustard seed together.
Heat to boiling point, but don't boil.
Cover cucumbers and onions with hot liquid.
Seal jars.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place sauerkraut in colander in sink.
Rinse with cold water.
Press to drain well.
Combine onion, soup, milk and mustard in a medium bowl.
Blend well.
Spread sauerkraut in prepared pan.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over noodles.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over the top of the casserole.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Blend mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
Measure out half of the soup mixture.
Combine with the ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt and 1 slightly beaten egg.
Shape into meatballs and brown in 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Add the remaining soup mixture and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Recipe can easily be halved.

title: pineapple angel pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and water until smooth.
Bring pineapple juice to a boil, then place in a double boiler.
Add flour mixture and cook for 15 minutes, stirring well.
Gradually add beaten egg yolks; stir quickly and remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate mixture overnight.
Pour into a pie shell; top with whipped heavy cream.
Serves 6.

title: indiana picnic cake
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Save one cup for topping.
Add rest of ingredients to remainder of mixture in bowl. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: country pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice in a small saucepan.
Set aside.
Add enough water to the juice to make 1 1/3 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl and add the boiling liquid. Stir to dissolve and cool until slightly thickened.
In a mixing bowl, add cream, gradually beating in sugar.
Fold into the gelatin mixture.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend well.
Pour into a 1 1/2 qt. serving bowl. Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: date roll
directions: Grind nuts and dates.
Add eggs and pinch of salt.
Mix all together and roll into small logs and roll in coconut.
Grease cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour dressing over all. Toss gently.
Let cool 1/2 hour and serve.

title: holiday punch
directions: In 10-quart punch bowl, dissolve sugar and drink mix in cold water.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Add rum or vodka.
Just before serving, add ice.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Layer
Mix graham crackers and butter; press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil until thick, about 5 minutes, the cornstarch, strawberry jello, sugar and hot water.
Cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Cut ends from stems of mushrooms; wash and slice the mushrooms.
Mix the remaining ingredients together; add the mushrooms and toss until pieces are well coated.
Let stand at room temperature for several hours.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: red hot punch
directions: Early in the day put red cinnamon hots and small can of pineapple juice in a bowl.
Cover and chill.
Chill other juices and ginger ale.
When ready to serve mix all ingredients in a punch bowl and serve.

title: ramen salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Mix next 5 ingredients and let stand a few minutes. Toss everything together and serve immediately.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring all ingredients (except popped corn and soda) to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes, remove from heat and add soda. Put popped corn into a large pan or roaster, pour cooked mixture over corn and stir well. Bake at 250° for one hour, uncovered. Cool, break apart and add peanuts. Freezes well.

title: german potato salad(serves 50)
directions: Place in a large roaster, heat 35 minutes at 350°.

title: gourmet strawberry preserves
directions: Berries with hollow cores should not be used.
Combine berries and sugar; let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Bring slowly to boiling, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves.
Cook rapidly until thick, about 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice and continue cooking 10 minutes longer.
Pour, boiling hot, into sterilized Ball jars. Adjust caps.
Yield:
About 4 half pints.

title: chicken patties
directions: Cook chicken in a crock-pot until done.
Pull chicken apart or cut up to desired consistency.
Grated cheese on top of chicken and sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Make oval patties and roll in crescent roll.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 can chicken broth from crock-pot real good. Pour some on each roll and the rest in the bottom of dish.

title: rolls
directions: In bowl, sift flour.
In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons water.
Add lukewarm water, shortening, sugar and egg. Slowly add flour; blend well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape the dough into rolls.
Let rise in warm place.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown on top.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, 1/2 cup crumbs, onions, 2 tablespoons oleo, salt and pepper.
Put into casserole.
Combine 1/2 cup crumbs and remaining oleo.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Drain and set aside.
Line the bottom of loaf pan with cheeses (1/3).
Layer 1/3 of noodles. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar; top with cheese.
Repeat process, ending with cheese.
Pour evaporated milk on top; salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Combine the gelatin, milk, sweetener and cream cheese in blender.
Cover and blend smooth. Add pudding mix, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Cover and blend smooth.
Spoon into pie shell and chill until set.

title: grilled rosemary pork roast
directions: In a saucepan combine the first six ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Place pork roast in a large resealable plastic bag; add half the marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Transfer remaining marinade to a bowl; cover and refrigerate.

title: delightful fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Cool.
Combine pecans and fruit; add dressing, stirring well.
Chill before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
May want to put bananas in just before serving.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Wash beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Arrange beans in a steaming rack placed over boiling water; cover and steam 8 to 10 minutes.
Plunge beans into cold water; drain and set aside.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until tender.
Add green beans and remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes or until heated.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix juices, adding some of the cherry juice and carbonated beverage in large punch bowl.
Add other ingredients, except for lemon, lime and sherbet.
Scoop sherbet by the spoonful to float on top of punch.
Use enough to almost cover the top.
Blend gently.
Place lemon, lime and mint sprigs in center for garnish.

title: wine pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with vermouth and milk.
Soak raisins in 1/2 water and 1/2 cup vermouth overnight.
Whip cream and fold into pudding with nuts and raisins (drained).
Pour filling into graham cracker pie shells.
Freeze until firm.
Top with whipped cream and allow to thaw slightly.

title: cinnamon spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together until creamy.
Chill before serving.
Yields 1 cup.

title: white chili
directions: Place beans in large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by at least 3 inches and soak overnight.
Place chicken in large saucepan.
Add cold water to cover and bring to simmer.
Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin.
Cut chicken into cubes.
Drain beans.
Heat oil in same pot over medium-high heat.
Add onions and saute until translucent, about 10 minutes.
Stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano, cloves and cayenne; saute 2 minutes.
Add beans and stock and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are very tender, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bring to simmer before continuing.

title: country stew (crock-pot)
directions: Combine all.
Put in crock-pot on high, 4 to 5 hours.

title: jello banana split
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Cut gelatin into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise into halves; remove seeds.
Cut each half into 1/2 inch slices.
Mix cucumbers, soup, water chestnuts and milk in 3 quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until cucumbers are tender, about 6 minutes. Stir in dill weed and pimento.
8 servings; 40 calories per serving.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Place chops in buttered baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with thinly sliced apple slices.
Sprinkle lemon juice and cover dish tightly. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Remove cover. Brush with butter and bake for 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: cheese-onion spread for crackers
directions: Blend everything except chutney and onions with electric beaters or with a food processor.
Spread in a shallow dish and chill until firm.
Spread chopped chutney on top and sprinkle onions on top of chutney.

title: ritz cracker torte
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
With rolling pin, crush Ritz crackers plus chopped nuts.
Fold this into egg whites.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool.

title: quick and easy banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mash bananas.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: granny gibbs' grape wine
directions: Chase wild bullfrogs 3 miles and gather up hops.
To them, add 10 gallons of tan bark, 1/2 pint of shellac and 1 bar of homemade soap.
Boil 36 hours, then strain through an I.W.W. (I won't work) sock to keep it from working.
Add 1 grasshopper to each pint to give it a kick.
Pour a little into the kitchen sink. If it takes the enamel off, it is ready for bottling.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together the hamburger, egg, salt, minced onion, catsup and Worcestershire sauce and shape into patties.

title: ben's sweet potato pie(this is for 3 pies)
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; mash when cooked.
Add potatoes, sugar and eggs and mix with spoon, then add flour, cinnamon, salt, vanilla flavoring and melted butter.
Mix in mixing bowl until smooth texture.
Then add in pie crust.
Cook 45 minutes at 450° in oven.
Can cook on 425°.
Preheat oven.

title: western-style brisket
directions: Wash and dry brisket.
Bring to room temperature and sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Place meat fat side up in roaster.
Combine catsup and horseradish.
Spread over meat.
Add water until about 1 inch deep.
Cover.
Cook 6 hours at 225°.
Cool and slice. Reheat slices in foil when ready to serve.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients, then add liquids.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: camembert appetizer
directions: Dip cheese in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Saute cheese in butter until inside of cheese is melted.
Remove from pan.
Saute chives in same pan for just a minute, then pour over cheese.
Serve with thin slices of French bread.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: italian beef pie
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces and brown slowly in a skillet.
Remove from pan.
Dredge the beef cubes in flour, salt and pepper; brown in the drippings in the skillet.
Remove from pan and set aside with sausage.
Saute onion in drippings.
Place onion, sausage and beef cubes in pot.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Place mixture in 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours and 20 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Sift first four ingredients, add milk, egg yolks and melted shortening.
Mix thoroughly,
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Cook on well-greased waffle iron.

title: best ever cheese cake
directions: Blend all ingredients; press against the bottom and sides of a spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple velvet
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in lemon juice and 1/4 cup pineapple syrup.
Chill until egg white consistency.
Fold in 1 cup well drained pineapple and almonds.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar, 1/8 teaspoon almond flavoring and 1/8 teaspoon salt to 1/2 cup whipping cream.
Beat until thick and fluffy.
Fold into gelatin and chill.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix ingredients. Let soak overnight.

title: yogurt dip
directions: Combine yogurt and Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit (strawberries, bananas, grapes, peach and pear slices) and/or vanilla wafers.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Melt margarine in 1 c. boiling water; add flour and a dash of salt; stir vigorously. Cook and stir till mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate; remove from heat and cool slightly. Add eggs and beat until smooth; stir in cheese. Drop dough onto greased baking sheet using 1 level tsp. dough for each puff. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes. Cool and split. Combine remaining ingredients and fill each puff.

title: fruit and cheese pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover a 14-inch pizza pan with aluminum foil.
Cut cookie dough into 1/8 to 1/4-inch rounds.
Arrange in slightly overlapping pattern, covering pan completely.
Press to seal.
Bake until puffed and golden, about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
(This can be done 8 hours ahead of time.)
Combine the cream cheese, sugar, brandy and vanilla in bowl; spread evenly over crust.
Arrange fruit slices in circular pattern over filling.
Start with strawberries, then kiwi, then bananas, repeating until completely filled.
Melt apricot preserves with the brandy in small saucepan over low heat; brush over fruit. Cover; chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and put into a greased loaf pan.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice lightly in oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until onion is transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 35 to 40 minutes until rice is done.

title: mary beth's sauerkraut balls
directions: Rice the potatoes, using a food ricer, into a large mixing bowl. Add the sauerkraut, ham, egg yolks and 1/4 cup of mustard. Mix well and season with salt and pepper. Form the mixture into small balls, about a tablespoon each. Place on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Freeze for 30 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to full boil; remove immediately from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and cereal.
Press into a greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread as icing over first mixture.

title: processor french bread
directions: Grease baguette pans or spray with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 c warm water and add 1 tsp. sugar.
Stir to dissolve.
Let stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes. Combine flour, salt, 1 tsp. sugar, and yeast mixture in work bowl of food processor.
With machine running, slowly add the 1/2 c warm water, adding more if necessary to form a soft ball.
Let machine run for about 1 minute.
(Add a few Tbsp. of flour if dough is too sticky.)
Transfer dough to floured board and knead for several turns.
(Not absolutely necessary if dough it to sticky to handle, or if you are in a hurry!)
Divide dough in half and shape into 2 long, thin cylinders, about 8 inches long.
Transfer to prepared pans and cut 3 or 4 diagonal slashes on top of each loaf with a razor blade.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450.
Put bread into the oven and immediately toss 1/4 c cold water onto oven floor and close door. Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400 and bake 15 minutes longer, or until loaves are golden brown.
Transfer to a rack to cool.

title: saucepan peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix Karo syrup in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil until you see bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: tradd street chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lemon slices.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Arrange lemon slices on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly (20 to 30 minutes).
Serves 8.
Can be prepared a day ahead.

title: grape concord wine
directions: Wash grapes and put in crock (a few green ones, too); crush. Add boiling water, cup for cup, the same amount as grapes.
Cover with cheesecloth.
Leave for 10 days.
Strain.
For 1 gallon of liquid, add 4 pounds of sugar, then let work for 2 weeks.
Bottle and put a balloon on bottle until it stops working, then drink. The longer you wait, the better it is, like 6 months or more.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine the cream cheese and milk, mixing well.
Add onion and horseradish.
Add crabmeat; stir lightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until hot.
Serve with snack crackers and fresh vegetables.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: In large bowl, combine the pudding mix, pineapple (undrained) and sour cream.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into pie crust. Garnish with listed ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.

title: sweet potatoes and apple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of yams and apples. Dot with margarine.
Bake for about 40 minutes.

title: perfect party punch
directions: Combine liquids and add thawed strawberries. Garnish with orange twists and whole strawberries.
Serves 48 people.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Mix in taco seasoning, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Place mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Microwave for 5 minutes on High.
Top with cheese and chips.
Microwave for 2 minutes more.
Serve with salad and baked potato.

title: new potatoes with roasted garlic
directions: Tear off a 36 x 18-inch piece of heavy foil.
Fold in half to make a double thickness of foil that measures 18 x 18-inches.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sliced potatoes, unreeled garlic cloves, 1 tablespoon olive oil and salt; toss gently.
Place potato mixture in the center of the foil.
Top with rosemary sprigs.
Bring up the two opposite edges of the foil and seal with a double fold.
Fold remaining ends to completely enclose the potato mixture, leaving space for steam to build.
Preheat gas grill.
Adjust heat for direct cooking.
Place foil packet on grill rack over medium heat.
Cover and grill about 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Discard rosemary sprigs.

title: angels on horseback(microwave)
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Arrange in two layers on paper towel with paper between layers and on top.
Cook 3 minutes until partially done. Drain oysters.
Dip each one in cream.
Roll in breadcrumbs mixed with seasonings.
Wrap each coated oyster in bacon and hold together with toothpick.
Roll again in coating. Arrange on paper plate, double paper toweling top and bottom. Cook 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: jackie's scalloped oysters
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Put a layer in bottom of a baking dish, then a layer of oysters.
Repeat and top with crumbs.
Never have more than 2 layers of oysters so they will cook evenly.
Pour milk over oysters and crumbs in the baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lobster stuffed tenderloin
directions: Have beef cut 1/2-inch thick to butterfly.
Parboil lobster 2 minutes.
Put lobster end to end inside meat and roll tightly.
Tie with string every 1-inch.
Roast at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes for rare.
Top with bacon for 5 more minutes.
Saute onion, garlic, lemon juice and wine for sauce.
Each slice in lobster surrounded by beef in wine sauce.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together the chicken, soup and cheese.
Drain vegetables; add to mixture.
Fix one pie crust in a 9-inch or a little bit bigger pie pan.
Pour mixture in, then top with other pie crust. Cut slits in top of crust.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: mock potato salad
directions: Boil cauliflower in salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain, cool and break into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: sausage cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough cold water to hold together. Shape into small balls; flatten. Bake at 400 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: lemon fruit splash
directions: In large punch bowl or pitcher, combine lemonade flavor crystals with orange slices.
Stir in cold water and grenadine. Chill at least 2 hours.
To serve, add remaining ingredients and if desired pour over ice.

title: caramel nut rolls(heritage recipe)
directions: In small sauce pan beat milk and butter until very warm.
In large bow combine warm liquid, 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast and egg; beat 4 minutes at medium speed. by hand, stir in remaining flour to form a stiff batter.
Cover, let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size (30 - 40 minutes).

title: company rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour soups together and mix well into baking dish.
Then add mushrooms and white rice.
Put into oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
VERY EASY!

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ketchup. Mix thoroughly.
Put mixture into oiled loaf pan and spread ketchup on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray a 4-cup baking dish with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In a large pot of rapidly boiling water, cook macaroni 8 to 10 minutes, until tender; drain.
Return macaroni to same pot and combine with remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into prepared dish; bake 15 to 18 minutes, until golden and bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Cut 1 stick margarine in slices.
Line long cake pan with waxed paper.
Put butter in pan and melt.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in melted butter in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt the 1/2 stick margarine and mix with softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
When mixed good, spoon over the cake mixture.
(I put about 4 or 5 spoons down each side and down middle when done.)
Turn out in long Tupperware box and spread icing mixture over cake.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and peanut butter together.
Can use the microwave oven.
Stir well and pour over Crispix cereal.
Put powdered sugar in large paper bag and shake to coat.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar together well.
Blend in egg. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add half of flour mixture, then add cherry juice and milk.
Stir in remaining flour mixture and mix well.
Blend in chocolate, nuts and cherries.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting and top with a cherry.

title: best corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan with part of the oil.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
If not brown, place under broiler briefly; watch carefully
so it doesn't burn.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Fold the cheese mixture into the pudding mixture and then fold in the Cool Whip. Use 8 to 10-inch plastic or ceramic flower pot (line bottom with foil).
Alternate layers of cookies and cheese mixture.
End with a cookie layer.
Arrange silk flower to make a beautiful blooming plant.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper. Add water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Do not drain.
Make a cream sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add corn and undrained vegetables.
Heat.
Do not boil.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Cut wieners into 10 pieces each.
Put into pot and add ketchup, barbecue sauce and sugar.
Stir and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Will serve 40 people easily.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together, except the buttered cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: granny's fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients. When ready to serve, add 1 quart ginger ale. Garnish with lemon slices and clove sticks.

title: pint 'o pickle
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a 4-quart bowl. Microwave 4 minutes, stirring once.
Add cucumber and onion slices.
Stir and cover with Saran Wrap.
Turn back edge to vent. Microwave 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Re-cover and microwave 2 minutes.
Let stand covered 10 minutes.
Spoon into jar.
Chill before serving.

title: crabmeat potato salad
directions: Combine the stock, potatoes and saffron in medium saucepan. Cook on high; bring to boil and cook until fork-tender.
Let set for about 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1/2 cup of the liquid.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Place in bottom of pan.
Layer with potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Spread dough over whole cookie sheet. Layer the center third of dough with cold cuts.
Saute onions and peppers in margarine and layer on top of cold cuts.
Sprinkle spices and cheese and spread mustard on top.
Cut each side of dough in 8 equal parts, cutting the edge of filling.
Fold strips to center, alternating sides.
Pinch together and seal to make a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Slice into equal slices.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown bacon and remove strips from pan. In grease, brown onion and bell pepper and add other ingredients. Simmer approximately 30 minutes or until it is desired consistency.

title: crab dip
directions: Warm soup; dissolve gelatin and add to soup.
Add softened cream cheese.
Add remainder of ingredients and pour into mold or plastic bowl.
Chill.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Brown and drain hamburger. Place nachos in 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer meat and taco seasoning. Mix soup and milk and spread over meat. Add other ingredients as desired and top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.

Add one egg at a time. Mix flour, honey, lemon juice, vanilla, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and fold in with butter and sugar. Then fold in raisins, dates, pecans, almonds, cherries and pineapple.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Top with orange twists to serve.
Serves 6.

title: coconut potato kisses
directions: Cream together the potatoes, butter, salt and flavoring.
Stir in sugar. Add coconut. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Cool until set.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Melt the Candi-quick and dip balls in chocolate.

title: marinated beef strips
directions: Cut meat in thin strips.
Separate onion into rings.
Combine beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn down TV; Brandon and Nathan like it loud!!!
Remove Hank's toys from the countertop.
Measure 2 cups flour.
Get baking powder; remove Luke's hands from flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter, after you take it away from Kyle.
Vacuum mixture off kitchen floor where Mandy spilled it.
Get an egg.
Ooops!
Natasha tripped you up.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers, then remaining pudding. Add another layer of crackers and refrigerate 1 hour.
Frost with Betty Crocker chocolate frosting.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine 1/2 Kool-Aid, 1/2 pineapple juice and 1/2 7-Up in a Jell-O ring.
Add any amount of cherries, chunk pineapple or fruit cocktail.
Freeze to form ice ring.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk and vanilla, using large mixing bowl.
Beat at high until topping thickens.
Add remaining milk and the pie/pudding filling mix; blend at low. Beat high for 2 minutes.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill for 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, horseradish, and drained shrimp. Shape into a ball.
Spread cocktail sauce over ball.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and rice until done, then drain.
Saute onion (chopped) with oleo until tender.
Mix all together and cook in oven until cheese melts.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cook the hot dogs in the microwave for 3 to 5 minutes.
Slice hot dogs, down the center, and put cheese inside.
Wrap the hot dog in a crescent roll.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes at 350°. Yummee!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and butter.
Layer bottom of pan with stuffing, 1 layer of chicken, can of mushroom soup, 1 cup chicken broth, layer stuffing, layer of chicken, can chicken soup and 1 cup chicken broth.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: katie's chocolate cheese cake
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with almond flavoring.
Keep warm.
In large bowl, beat softened cream cheese.
Blend in sour cream and eggs, one at a time.
Add melted chocolate until well mixed.
Pour into cracker crusts and bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: fourth of july cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and NutraSweet.
Pat evenly on bottom of jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle gelatin on top of milk in small saucepan.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool to room temperature. Beat cream cheese in large bowl until creamy.
Gradually beat in milk mixture.
Beat in lemon juice, rind, vanilla and 1/3 to 1/2 cup NutraSweet.
Pour mixture over crust and refrigerate until set.

title: a b c pancakes(children's)
directions: Combine egg, milk and oil in bowl and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together into bowl.
Stir flour mixture into liquid mixture just until mixed.
Drizzle 1 teaspoon of batter into letters on hot griddle.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Be careful when you turn the letters.
Pour rest of batter over and around letters to make pancakes the size you like.
Brown pancakes on both sides.

title: oreo party pops
directions: Insert sticks into cream center of each cookie. Heat chocolate and oil in small sauce pan over low heat. Stirring constantly until melted and smooth. dip each cookie into melted chocolate to coat. Place on waxed paper. Decorate with sprinkles or candies.

title: tuna patties
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/3 cup potato flakes and margarine.
Form mixture into 6 patties.
Coat both sides with 1/3 cup mashed potato flakes.
Melt margarine in skillet and fry patties until deep golden brown on both sides.

title: golden spoon bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Combine eggs and milk; stir into cornmeal mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown meat with salt.
Drain beans.
Cut up other ingredients for salad and toss all together.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Mix cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Dip shrimp in egg batter.
Roll in flour.
Drop battered shrimp in hot Crisco or oil.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown or golden.
(A 2-quart boiler can be used instead of frypan.)
Do not overcook.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add baking powder to flour, then add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french bread
directions: Mix yeast with water; let set 10 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients and mix with yeast mixture after it sets 10 minutes. Cover; let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch down, divide in half.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, not stiff.
Add other ingredients.
Mix in pecans.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet. Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir occasionally.

title: bacon horseradish dip(hot hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir to mix well.
Cover and chill. Makes 2 cups.
Serve with any type crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the apples, pecans and raisins.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Add apples, pecans and raisins and stir well.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with greased wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hour.

title: berries and cream
directions: Mix the sugar and gelatin in a small saucepan. Add the water and stir over low heat to dissolve the sugar and gelatin. Remove from heat; pour into a bowl and blend in the sour cream and vanilla. Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip the cream until thick; fold into sour cream mixture.
Pour into a 1-quart mold and chill until firm, about 3 hours. Unmold the cream onto a plate. Pour the fresh fruit over it.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake according to box directions.

title: grated potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish (greased). Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked apple
directions: Core apple and place on baking sheet.
Put pop in apple.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Real good with diet pop.

title: peanut butter balls snack
directions: Mix together, mold into small balls (about 1 teaspoon).
Roll in wheat germ.

title: chuck wagon salad
directions: Drain and rinse macaroni and drain again.
Drain three bean salad, reserving 1 tablespoon of the liquid.
Stir together mayonnaise and reserved liquid.
Mix all.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: gramma's casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
In saucepan, heat soup, milk and cheese, stirring, until well mixed.
In greased casserole, place a layer of noodles, hamburg mixture and milk mixture alternately. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Form into 40 bite-size balls (using a full teaspoon for each).
Brown meatballs lightly in oil. Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: banana milkshake no. 1
directions: Blend all ingredients, except ice cubes, in blender container. Add ice cubes, one at a time, and process after each addition. Makes 2 servings.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cut carrots into thin strips.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Place cooked carrots in a buttered baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over top and stir.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snickers cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat together butter, peanut butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to peanut butter mixture until combined.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter until fluffy; add sugar, continuing to cream. Add eggs and sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed ingredients.
Chill well.
Roll out and cut in desired shapes; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bronchitis medicine
directions: Put in bottle about 6-inches tall and fill to about 3/4 full of water.
Add all of the ingredients.
Shake to mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: so-easy sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, margarine or shortening, oil, milk, almond extract and egg until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Spread evenly in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes; cut into bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: quick lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and thawed lemonade.
Fold in 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Combine well.
Pour into crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: baked chuck roast
directions: Place roast on foil in baking pan.
Spoon soup over roast. Sprinkle
onion soup mix on top.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: cherry go round
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast to warm water and stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture; beat well.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of the bowl.
Knead until smooth and satiny on lightly floured board.
Place in greased bowl; invert to grease top. Cover and let rise until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Crush red hots in blender.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a quart jar.
Add boiling water to 2 heaping teaspoons in coffee cup.
Serve.

title: fried okra(easy)
directions: Heat oil until hot.
Roll okra in (corn meal, cornstarch, salt and sugar) mixture.
Have oven hot and ready at 400°.
Stir often until brown and tender.

title: red sauce
directions: Mix together mustard, sugar and water, leaving no lumps.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to slight boil.
After chops are tender, remove from oven and dip in red sauce.
After dipping, bake 30 minutes more at 350° or until slightly glazed.

title: dr. hicks' favorite red beans and rice
directions: Brown and drain fat of sausage.
Brown 1 cup chopped onions in olive oil.
Add garlic, parsley, Tabasco sauce, beans and sausage all together in skillet or pan and simmer to blend flavors.
Use water in can of beans; add one cup of water. Simmer on low for approximately 10 minutes while cooking rice. Serve over rice.
Serve with extra Tabasco sauce if desired. Don't simmer until dry or will be without some sauce for rice.

title: cilantro and lime slaw
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add cilantro and Lime Vinaigrette.

title: alice cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar; add eggs and milk, then coconut, raisins and nuts.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour; mix.
Add oatmeal and stir into liquid ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southern buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour (sift if desired) together with shortening and work to consistency of cornmeal.
I use a pastry blender.
Add other ingredients and then add buttermilk; stir in well.
Turn out on floured surface (wax paper saves a mess).
Knead only until it can be rolled.
Roll using rolling pin to 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits with cutter.
Bake on greased pan for 8 to 10 minutes at 450° oven.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
This will be a hit with your yankee friends!

title: roast wild duck
directions: Stir together salt, pepper and rosemary.
Sprinkle mixture inside and outside of ducks.
Stuff each bird with 4 pieces each of onion, apple and celery, and some butter.
Place, breast side down, on roasting pan rack.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Baste frequently.
Ducks are done when juices are no longer pink.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Then add vegetables and cook until carrots are soft.

title: basic yeast dough
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and 1/2 cup water. Add yeast which has been softened in 1/2 cup water.
Add flour gradually, mixing it in thoroughly.
When dough is stiff, turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Shape into ball. Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until dough is double in bulk.
Punch down.
Let rise again. Mold into loaves.
Place in greased bread pans.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in moderately hot oven (400° to 425°) for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: curried fruit(side dish)
directions: Drain fruit well; combine in a buttered ovenproof baking dish. Cook sugar, butter and curry in saucepan until melted.
Pour over fruit; refrigerate for a few hours.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange
chicken in one layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle generously
with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° until chicken is tender.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Butter baking dish and cover bottom with sliced potatoes.
Top with a layer of onions, then a layer of peppers and a layer of ham. Repeat until dish is full, ending with a layer of potatoes.
Beat egg with milk; season to taste and add to casserole.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Stick back in oven to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry banana pudding
directions: Line dish with wafers.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Pour over wafers.
Slice bananas; place on top of pudding.
Pour strawberries over bananas.
Spoon in Cool Whip over top.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours, covered, before serving.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade, milk and Cool Whip together in bowl. Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serves 6 people.

title: potato skins
directions: Thoroughly scrub potatoes; prick several times with a fork. Bake at 450 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done; allow to cool to touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp (carefully), leaving 1/8-inch thick shells.
Reserve pulp.
Cut each potato shell lengthwise into 4 strips and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Spray strips lightly with cooking spray.
Mix salt, paprika and pepper and sprinkle over strips.
Bake at 425 degrees for 14 minutes or until crisp.
In a small bowl combine yogurt, sour cream and chives.
Serve potato skins with sour cream mixture. Yields 32 appetizers:
one potato skin and 3/4 teaspoon dip each.

title: pecan loaf cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each egg until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans. Pour into loaf pan or Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° at least 1 hour and 15 minutes in loaf pan or until toothpick comes out clean.
If using a Bundt pan, cook for about 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: date nut cake
directions: Combine boiling water, soda and dates.
Cream sugar and shortening and add egg.
Stir in rest of ingredients and add date mixture last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: wieners and peppers
directions: Mix.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put in jars.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: microwave mini reubens
directions: Combine all ingredients except toast.
Refrigerate prior to serving.
Five minutes before serving, place heaping teaspoonful on Melba toast.
Microwave (10 at a time) for 40 to 50 seconds on Medium-high.

title: bob andy pies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then flour and cream.
Mix and pour into unbaked crusts (2).
Bake slowly at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: gramp's farm baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients 3 or 4 times.
Cut in butter until well mixed.
Add milk.
Stir well.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Sprinkle very lightly with flour to avoid sticking to hands and shape into smooth ball.
Roll lightly and pat 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan and bake in a hot oven for 15 minutes, 400° to 425° in wood range.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla, buttermilk and grated zucchini.
Blend well. Sift together all the dry ingredients and mix into the liquid mixture. Put in a 9 x 13-inch floured pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts on top of batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add nuts.
Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, blending thoroughly with each addition.

title: baked sirloin tips
directions: Pour over mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: icing-uncooked
directions: Place all ingredients over hot water for 10 minutes.
Beat icing until cool and a smooth consistency.
Frosts 1 cake.

title: canned green peppers
directions: Wash and core enough peppers to fill 2 pint jars (sliced in strips).
Pack into sterilized jars.
Combine all ingredients. Bring to full rolling boil.
Pour over peppers.
Seal at once, leaving rings on caps after they seal.

title: basil pork chops(for diabetics)
directions: Trim and discard excess fat from chops.
In a large frying pan, brown chops without excess fat.
When chops are brown, add other ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer 40 minutes or until tender. Turn meat occasionally and add a few tablespoons of water if necessary to avoid burning.
One serving equals 1 chop plus 1 tablespoon sauce.

title: oven corn chips
directions: Stack tortillas and using a sharp knife cut through centers to make 6 sections.
Arrange wedges, without overlapping, on baking sheets that have been lightly sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Lightly spray arranged edges.
Sprinkle with seasoning of choice. Bake at 400° for approximately 8 minutes or until lightly browned and crisp.
Store in airtight plastic bags after cooling. Serve with salsa or low-fat dip.

title: fresh cucumber salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed in microwave safe dish and microwave on high one minute to heat.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a medium pot.
Add water, food coloring and oil.
Stir over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
When the mixture forms a ball in the center of the pot, take it out and put it on a floured surface.
Squish it and punch in around a bit.
This is called kneading.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer 30 minutes.

title: fudge cake brownies
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Stir by hand. Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Stir just until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Sift powdered sugar on top and remove from pan.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and beat.
Pat out biscuits.
Put in 450° oven for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: granola bars
directions: In large bowl combine cereal, rolled oats, raisins, chocolate bits and nuts.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, combine brown sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla; blend until smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes approximately 20 bars.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, milk, spices and bread crumbs.
Divide into 8 equal portions.
Pat each portion into 4 x 5-inch rectangle.
Place cheese, mushrooms and onion in center of each of 4 rectangles. Place remaining 4 rectangles on top and seal edges securely. Smooth over any openings or cracks.
Place on jelly roll pan or broiler pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onions and potatoes until tender. Cut up meat in bite size pieces.
Combine milk, flour and butter. Cook over low heat until thick.
Add salt and pepper to white sauce.
Drain potatoes.
Combine potatoes, onions and meat together.
Pour white sauce over it, then sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix the Jell-O, cornstarch and sugar together and set aside. In saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to boil.
Slowly add dry Jell-O mixture, stirring constantly to blend.
Bring to second boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.
Arrange fresh berries in baked pie shell.
Pour cooled filling over berries. Refrigerate at least 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: quick french bean soup
directions: Simmer on stove for 2 hours or in a crock-pot.

title: french toast
directions: Place butter in frying pan.
Dip bread in mix; place in frying pan.
Cook until brown.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into one-fourth inch slices.
Precook 5 minutes in boiling water (salted).
Drain.
Layer potatoes, bacon and onion in a greased, shallow, 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine in a pan.
Stir in flour, 1 1/4 teaspoons salt, pepper and celery seed.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Spoon cheese mixture over potatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cream and salt until soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and mix thoroughly. Pour into buttered dish.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and chopped onions to taste.
Add frozen vegetables and pour on soup. Top with Tater Tots and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: original toll house cookies
directions: Blend butter with sugars; add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and a few drops of hot water.
Mix together until well blended.
Lastly add chopped nuts, chocolate and vanilla.
Drop by half teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: big soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°; lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Blend in milk, 2 eggs and oil.
Add sugar, salt and 5 cups flour (1 cup at a time) and stir well.
Add 1 cup flour gradually to make a soft, but not sticky dough.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together and refrigerate for a couple of hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: country corn
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas morning sausage ring
directions: Combine ingredients; Mix well.
Pack lightly into greased 6-cup ring mold; Chill several hours.
Unmold into jelly roll pan.
Bake in 325° gas oven for 1 hr.
Serve with scramble eggs in center. Makes 12 servings

title: beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package.
Put aside. Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper together.
Stir in macaroni and cheese and mushroom soup.
Does not need to be baked since everything is already cooked.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Mix together and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large soup pot. Drain well. Add all ingredients except last four (cabbage, green beans, macaroni and Parmesan). Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes. Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni. Simmer until done. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Dream Whip, eggs and water for 4 minutes.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool cake 15 minutes.
Poke holes on top of cake with big meat fork.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Use wooden spoon only to mix.
Mix sugars and cinnamon. Reserve 3/4 cup for topping and nuts.
Mix all ingredients well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add nuts to 3/4 cup topping; sprinkle over batter, cutting into mix with knife.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken-cashew casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Put into casserole 1 1/2 cans chow mein noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Put remaining 1/2 can chow mein noodles.
May need to add a little water or milk as it's baking.

title: southwestern soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Be sure to put soda in hot applesauce.
Cream shortening with sugar, then add apples.
Sift flour and spices together and mix raisins in flour.
Add to apples and sugar.
Add walnuts last. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased and floured pan.

title: rebecca's stew
directions: Brown meat
in	3 tablespoons of oil.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot or simmer all day in a large pan.

title: bachelor button cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Add pecans and coconut.
Roll in balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: lemon supreme special
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add dash of Worcestershire sauce, tomato ketchup and drained tomato juice to moisten casserole. Cover with cheese; heat just to melt cheese.

title: pumpkin cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Beat oil and eggs well.
Add sugar substitute and beat until light and fluffy; add pumpkin, then dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen after baking.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Use a jelly roll pan.
Spread cream cheese on the bottom. Pour/spread taco sauce, then cut up tomato, onion and pepper. Grate cheese and slice olives on the top.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Doritos, Tostitos or crackers.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix in small bowl the cocoa, sugar and hot water.
Stir! Add to milk in saucepan.
Stir occasionally.
Heat to desired temperature.
Pour into cups.
Add marshmallows.

title: best-ever salad(must blend for at least 10 hours.)
directions: You can make 2 days ahead and refrigerate!

title: orange julius
directions: Use a 5 or 5 1/2 cup-size blender.
Pour in all ingredients in order listed.
Blend until ice cream becomes slush.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.
Drink slowly.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt oleo and pour over flour and sugar.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: robbie's cinnamon bran muffins
directions: In large bowl stir cereal with water; moisten evenly.
Set aside to cool.
Stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: easy chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, water and juice all together; add chicken.
Marinate 24 hours, then place chicken single layered in a pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pasta supreme
directions: Cook and drain the noodles. Mix remaining ingredients and add noodles.

title: jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken until done (about 1 hour).
Let it cool enough to take skin off and debone it.
Save broth.
Put chicken meat back into broth.
In six cups of chicken broth, add rice, oil, bay leaves, Tabasco sauce, black pepper, cayenne pepper and onion. After water returns to boiling, cook for about 30 minutes.
Then add sausage and peas.
Cook another 30 minutes on medium heat, covered.

title: perfect tuna casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with chips; bake 5 minutes more, or until hot.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press on sides and bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.
Whip 1 cup whipping cream and chill.
In top of a double boiler, combine milk and miniature marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Add creme de menthe and creme de cacao. Fold in whipping cream.
Put softened ice cream on cookie crust.
Spread mixture on ice cream and freeze.

title: hamburger upside-down casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oleo.
Add ground chuck and cook until almost done.
Drain off grease.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer a few minutes.
Pour meat mixture into large baking dish.
Toss together macaroni and cheese; spread on top of meat.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: country-style steak
directions: Cut steak into several servings.
May have cubed at market or beat with hammer or mallet which makes servings larger and tender. Next, salt, pepper and coat with dry flour.
With small amount of oil in frypan (3 tablespoons approximately), brown steak.
Add sage and approximately 1/2 cup water.
Place lid on pan and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
May add water as needed, as this makes gravy for rice or potatoes served with steak.

title: native american cinnamon wild rice pudding
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, dried cherries or raisins, maple syrup, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, rice and half and half.
Stir gently.
Pour into casserole.

title: away all day chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in crock-pot on high.
Place cheese slices on chicken.
Mix soup and mayonnaise, pour on top of chicken.
Bake on high about one hour.
Turn down crock-pot to low and cook for 4 or 5 hours.
Check for tenderness.
Serve with rice or noodles!

title: potatoes and beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and cook onions until tender in water.
Add 1 cup water and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 minutes.

title: venison steak
directions: Pound the steak and coat with the flour and seasoning mixture. Heat skillet and add margarine and steak.
Brown the steak and add the mushroom soup with 1 can of milk or water.
Simmer until tender and gravy is thick.

title: crispy easter nests
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Add noodles and chopped chocolate candies. Mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Shape with greased fingers to form nests with hollow centers.
Let stand until firm.
Dust bottoms of nests with powdered sugar, if desired. Fill with candies.
Makes 10 or 12 nests.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Stir well.
If too thick, add a bit of cream or milk.
Store in refrigerator.

title: wheat germ corn bread
directions: About 2 hours before serving or early in the day:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease well a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, with a fork, beat buttermilk, oil and eggs.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture, just until flour is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy, not smooth.)
Quickly pour into loaf pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool bread completely on wire rack to serve later.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put stuffing in baking dish.
Add zucchini, onions and carrots.
Mix soup, sour cream and butter.
Pour over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until done and leave plenty of liquid.
Add sugar. Mix egg yolks, milk and cornstarch together; add to rice and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. Top with Cool Whip or egg icing.
Keep in fridge.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs slightly.
Put in oven
and bake slowly at 300°
about 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over spareribs.
Baste meat with sauce.
Bake until well done, about 1 1/2 hours longer.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: In pan, cook onion, garlic and butter for about 5 minutes. Add broth, cabbage, caraway, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add cooked noodles to hot cabbage and mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Drain caps and chop stems and reserve.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, pepperoni, green peppers, garlic and stems.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, seasoned salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in chicken broth.
Spoon stuffing into caps.
Place in shallow baking pan with 1/4-inch water.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: seven-up apple dumplings
directions: Combine 7-Up, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and margarine.
Cook until sugar is dissolved and butter is melted.
Remove and let cool.
Cool and pare 6 apples, leaving whole.
Mix 6 tablespoons sugar with 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Sift together dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add milk.
Roll out like pie dough and cut into 7-inch squares.
Place apples in squares.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Fold dough over.
Place in baking dish and pour 7-Up mixture over all apples.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mississippi special
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the onion in the water until it softens.
Add the beer and catfish and cook over medium heat until done (3 to 5 minutes).
Combine the cooked rice, catfish/onion mixture, chopped tomatoes, spices and the peas.
Place in 8-inch square microwave dish and heat in microwave on Medium power for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes until heated through.
