If more moisture is needed, add more chopped tomatoes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Store tightly in glass jars.
Will keep in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries, pineapple, banana and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in loaf pan and put in freezer.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls; bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Boil to rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oats.
Mix well.
Drop on buttered pan.
Refrigerate.

title: wokking chef's salad
directions: For dressing, in small bowl stir together oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Cut watermelon and make into basket.
Scoop watermelon out with melon scoop.
Set aside.
Save juice.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with electric mixer. Mix in flour, walnuts, vanilla and salt.
Roll into balls, or shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
While still warm, roll in additional powdered sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine and shake well in quart jar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken martino
directions: Use 5-quart saucepan to brown chicken breasts in.
Dredge chicken breasts in flour and brown lightly in the butter (margarine).
Remove chicken and put into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sliced peppers and onions and pour the sherry over all.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tarter until foamy.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Pour over pie and bake about 10 minutes at 400°, until light brown.

title: easy chicken curry(yield:  4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Heat oil in a pan.
Cook onion, garlic and ginger pastes until golden brown.

title: chili steaks
directions: Combine flour and chili sauce in plastic bag.
Pound meat and add to bag.
Shake until coated.
Pour oil in 7 1/2 x 12-inch utility dish.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Add meat.
Turn to coat both sides with hot oil.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir. Add onion, tomatoes, chili with beans and salt.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on low for 25 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on High for 30 seconds.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter stars
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Stir in sifted flour mixture.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon of mixture into a ball, then roll ball in sugar.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Place candy Kiss in middle of each cookie and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cereal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat Karo and sugar.
Turn fire off.
Add peanut butter.

title: wine punch
directions: Pour all of wine into pitcher.
Pour same amount of 7-Up, cherries and juice, orange slices and sugar (for taste, if needed).
Pour over ice.

title: pheasant casserole
directions: Roll pheasant pieces in flour and brown in small amount of butter or oil in heavy skillet. Line the bottom and sides of a casserole with tomato slices.
Place pheasant pieces on top of tomato slices in casserole. Marinate dried mushrooms in a separate bowl of consomme.
When thoroughly soaked, drain mushrooms and add consomme to skillet fryings to make gravy.
Thicken to desired consistency.
Pour gravy over pheasant.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove lid. Add mushrooms and sherry to flavor (use your own judgment). Bake another hour in a 350° oven. Serve with steamed rice and pour gravy over all.

title: pork or turkey barbecue
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden brown.
Shred meat with fork.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve on bun.

title: fudge
directions: Cooking time is 15 minutes after the first ball can be rolled. Cut heat down to medium.

title: broccoli and grape salad
directions: Mix first the sugar, vinegar and mayo.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Put in bowl; mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: schnitz un gnepp
directions: Cover the dried apples with water and soak overnight.
Next day, cook ham slowly 2 hours.
Add apples and water in which they were soaked.
Add brown sugar and cook 1 hour.
Add gnepp last 20 minutes.

title: deviled pecans
directions: Melt margarine in pan; stir in salt, onion salt and chili powder. Stir in pecans making sure to coat well. Spread in 15 X 10 X 1 inch baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. Drain and cool on paper towels, serve as an appetizer.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese; mix until well blended.
Add other ingredients except pecans and blend well.
Shape into a ball.
Cover and chill at least 24 hours.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Yields 24 servings.

title: sedgwick style foiled potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into julienne strips, as for French fries.
Divide on 4 squares of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle each pile with onion salt, celery salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese as uniformly as possible.
Then dot each with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Close foil loosely, allowing room for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Put sugar, flour and cornmeal in a large bowl; toss lightly with a fork.
Add eggs, butter, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice. Beat with electric mixer until smooth and thoroughly blended. Pour into large pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and put in large soup pot.
Add all of the ingredients, except carrots.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: 90 minute rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120°.
Gradually add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide into 12 pieces.
Shape into balls and lightly pat out.
Place on greased pan.
Cover and place in warm spot and let rise until double. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: grape-nut pudding(microwave)
directions: Scald milk in 2-quart microproof bowl for 5 to 5 1/2 minutes on High (max power). Add Grape-Nuts. Let stand 5 to 7 minutes to soften Grape-Nuts. Add beaten eggs and sugar.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Place prepared cucumbers and onion in container.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into cucumbers and onion.
Store in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Very good.

title: glamour dogs
directions: Mix together the Fritos, grated cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and the tomato sauce.
Split frankfurters lengthwise and fill with the above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Mix the beans and chilies. Spread on serving tray.
Mash the avocados and mix with lemon juice. Spread over beans.
Blend mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread over the avocados.
Spread Cheddar and Jack cheeses over the mayonnaise layer. Spread onions over the cheese layer.
Spread olives over the onion layer. Remove seeds from tomatoes, dice and pat very dry; spread over olive layer.
Serve with chips.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and add marshmallows while hot.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: rice yeast bread(makes either 2 loaves or 24 rolls)
directions: *If milk is pasteurized it is unnecessary to scald it, but do heat it to lukewarm, about 110°.

title: cherry winks
directions: Beat butter 30 seconds, add sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat until well mixed and fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat until well combined, gradually add flour.
Beat again.
Stir in nuts and 1/3 cup cherries.
Put cereal in shallow dish, drop rounded teaspoon of dough into cereal and turn to coat.
Put 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, flatten slightly.
Press cherry quarters into center of each cookie.
Bake in 375° oven approximately 8 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Yield: 48 cookies.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and pecans in the bottom.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter over coconut and pecans.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Knead out lightly and wrap tightly.
Chill in the refrigerator.
Roll dough thin.
Fill with cooked dry fruits of your choice.
Fry in cooking oil at 375°.

title: kool-aid popsicles
directions: Make the Kool-Aid.
Pour in ice cube tray.
Stick in popsicle sticks.
Let sit in freezer overnight.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop and blend all ingredients and chill.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Combine butter, Crisco and sugar.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
When cake is finished baking, poke holes in top of cake.
Pour can of condensed milk and caramel syrup over top.
Refrigerate until completely cooled.

title: stir-fried vegetables with curry
directions: Add oil to heavy skillet or wok and heat to medium-high for 1 minute.
Add garlic; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add cabbage, celery and green onions.
Stir-fry 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chicken loaf for 100
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 4 large
greased	pans
at 325° for 1 hour.
Cut in squares, top with
tablespoon mushroom sauce.

title: smoky lemon garlic barbecue chicken
directions: If you're on a diet, remove the skin from the chicken.
Place the chicken parts into a large mixing bowl.
Add the olive oil. Dice the garlic.
Slice off 2 or 3 slices of lemon and dice them as well (peel and all).
Add garlic and lemon to the chicken and olive oil.

Take what's remaining of the lemon and juice it into the bowl, then scrape the remaining pulp into the bowl as well. Let sit, covered, at room temperature for about 3 hours, stirring about every 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together broth, celery soup, green peas and carrots. Add chicken and pour into casserole dish. Mix together oleo, milk and flour. Pour over chicken mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large microwavable bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Or heat in heavy saucepan over very low heat. Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with sauerkraut.
Pour juice over kraut and chops.
Top with onion and bell pepper.
Use seasoned salt to taste.
Wrap corn-on-the-cob in aluminum foil and place on top of onions and bell pepper.
Cover.

title: southern living's fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Store in airtight container. Use 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon per cup of boiling water.

title: tuna stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut thin slice from one flat side of each potato.
Scoop out the interior of the potatoes into a bowl.
Mash, adding the hot milk.
Whip until fluffy.
Add green onions, egg and butter.
Whip mixture well.
Season with salt and cayenne.
Fold in tomato and tuna.
Pile this mixture back into the potato skins, moulding it high.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until potatoes are heated through.

title: fruit mixture
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator.

title: caramel pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, butter and egg.
Mix at high speed until crumbly.
Press into pan.
Beat milk, egg and vanilla until blended.
Stir in pecans and Bits 'O Brickle chips.
Pour over cake base in pan; spread to cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Center will set upon cooling.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in order given in large casserole dish.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream, mixing well. Spread evenly over top of layered ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture, then sprinkle bacon bits over all.
Cover and chill for 6 hours.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
Lay pieces of
chicken
on rice.
Combine the soups and the water and pour over the chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add salt
and pepper
to	taste.	(Fast
and
easy for those busy evenings.)

title: aunt julia's french gulletts
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add cinnamon, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold in flour a little at a time.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator.
Bake in pizzelle iron.
Makes 12 to 13 dozen.

title: gold mine oat nuggets
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in egg and pineapple, including syrup.
Combine oats, flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon.
Stir into pineapple mixture with nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12-15 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: my applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar and add remaining ingredients. Pour into well buttered pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Take jello and mix until creamy.
Beat chilled milk and add to mixture.
Put in graham cracker pie crust.
Chill one hour before serving.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Grease casserole and layer:

title: buttermilk nutmeg cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add eggs and stir.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add to sugar/butter mixture, alternate with buttermilk and mix well.
Pour batter into two 9-inch layer pans.
Sprinkle tops of cake batter with sugar and nutmeg.
Bake 35 minutes or until done at 350°.
No frosting necessary.
The sugar and nutmeg make a sweet topping.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well.
Add 6 cups of bread flour.
Beat and mix well. Grease large bowl; pour batter in and turn over to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let sit overnight.

title: unbaked caramel cookies
directions: Combine
sugar, margarine and milk.
Stir over low heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and
add pudding
mix and oatmeal.
Stir thoroughly.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful
onto waxed paper.
These are really like candy!

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese, sugar, milk and pudding in blender.
Fold in whipped topping.
Alternate layers of cookie crumbs and creamy mixture.
Sprinkle the top of cake with crumbs to look like soil.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until browned.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper and chili sauce and put in casserole dish.
Add cheese next and put biscuits on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: divinity
directions: Put sugar, white Karo, water and salt into pan and stir well. Cook, without stirring, to 148°.
Beat egg whites until dry.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg whites.
Keep adding until all Karo is mixed in whites.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: date logs
directions: Cook dates,
sugar,
eggs,
oleo and salt over low heat for 10	minutes,
stirring continuously.
Place Rice Krispies and nuts in	bowl;
pour
hot mixture over and mix.	Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, cream cheese, egg and butter or margarine.
Layer in 8-inch cake pan:
noodles, tomato sauce, cheese mixture and half cheese.
Repeat except for cheese.
(You may have to adjust, depending on noodles.) Pour 1/2 cup water over it.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Remove foil.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: favorite chicken
directions: Place rice and onion soup mix in bottom of greased large flat baking dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and water and pour over top.
Cover tightly. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese.
Return, uncovered, to oven to melt cheese.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook
celery
and
onion
in
butter
until just tender; blend in flour.
Butter toast; cut in 1/2 inch cubes.
In 1 1/2 quart casserole,	combine
the onion-celery mixture with tomatoes, half the toast cubes, sugar and seasonings.
Bake at 350° for
30 minutes.
Top casserole with remaining toast cubes and bake 20 minutes longer.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and stir in pumpkin.
Alternate adding flour with water about 3 times until all is used.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Take the first 4 ingredients and cook until thick like custard.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and egg whites.
Pack some of the crushed wafers in bottom of freezing tray.
Add other ingredients and then sprinkle rest of crumbs on top; freeze.

title: 9 layer "iced" salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix lettuce and olives as first layer.
Layer next 8 ingredients, beginning with cucumbers and ending with cheese.
"Ice" salad with mixture of sour cream and dressing mix. Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar in mixing bowl. Tie spices in small cloth. Drop in vinegar mixture.
Slice pickles.
Rinse and drain well.
Add to mixture and let stand 4 hours. Stir once in awhile. Put half of sliced pickles in jars and add spices. Add rest of pickles and vinegar. Set in refrigerator for 4 days.

title: roast pork loin
directions: Combine garlic, ginger, soy sauce, white vinegar, brown sugar and chicken broth or water in plastic bag or bowl; add pork. Marinate 30 minutes or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roast in a lightly greased roasting pan for 1 hour, basting occasionally with marinade.
Slice thin and serve with rice and asparagus or salad. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave carrot cake
directions: Mix and beat well.

title: bread 'n butter microwave pickles
directions: Microwave on High 8 minutes, stirring well 2 times.
Ladle into jar.
Let cool, cover and refrigerate.
(Refrigerates up to 4 months.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream 2 cheeses together.
Add other ingredients and roll in pecans.
Eat on Ritz crackers.

title: cabbage in cheese sauce
directions: Put all ingredients except cabbage in a blender and blend together.
Cook cabbage in small amount of water until just tender.
Heat sauce and pour over cooked drained cabbage.

title: fungi(virgin island native recipe)
directions: To rapidly boiling water, add salt and sprinkle corn meal in slowly.
Allow water to boil over meal a few minutes.
Stir briskly to prevent lumping.
When well combined, add shortening.
Cover; steam about 5 minutes stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
Young okras may be added.
Cut into small pieces and allow to boil for a few minutes before adding meal.
A favorite variation which is very common to the natives is:

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: snow white buttermilk ice cream
directions: Combine all and freeze.

title: egg salad sandwich
directions: In a food processor or blender, whirl the tofu, mustard and water for about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Transfer the mixture to a medium size bowl and add the egg, egg whites, onion, red pepper, turmeric, paprika, salt and black pepper.
Toss to mix.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Melt peanut butter and
margarine
in
microwave
for 1 minute.
Add remaining
ingredients.
Stir until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 9 x
13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: nut pumpkin custard
directions: Separate eggs, using whites for topping on pie (meringue). Beat egg yolks, pecans and milk. Pour into a shallow baking dish so mixture will be two inches thick. Bake in slow oven (300° to 350°) until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: a quick and hardy meal
directions: If using deer meat, combine with other ingredients and cook until pasta is tender.
If using hamburger, brown and drain.
Add all other ingredients and cook until pasta is tender.
You may also add chopped onion to hamburger, if desired.

title: chili macaroni
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix and shape into patties.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Let set for about 10 minutes. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 35 minutes.

title: baked coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Add warm milk, shortening, beaten eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir and mix well.
Then turn out on floured board and knead.
This dough will be very soft, knead well, put it into a large greased bowl and cover with towel.
Place in warm oven.
Let it raise until doubled.
Punch it down and divide in 3 and knead.
Put in three 9 or 10-inch pans.
Spread melted butter over the top and sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 25 to 30 minutes.
You can ice the top or put fresh fruit on top.

title: eggplant-parmesan gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees.
Slice eggplants in half lengthwise.
Working with each eggplant half cut side up, make a 1 inch deep slit lengthwise down the middle to within 1 inch of each end (this makes the eggplant cook evenly).
Place eggplant halves cut sides down on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 475 degrees for 35 minutes or until tender.
Remove from oven; cool on pan 10 minutes.
Peel eggplant halves; cut crosswise into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes or until slightly thick, stirring frequently.
(Mixture will have a pasty consistency.) Stir in basil and pepper.
Spoon tomato mixture into a food processor; process for 1 minute, or until smooth.
Set aside. Reduce oven temperature to 425 degrees.
Arrange 1/2 of eggplant slices in a 9- by 13-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Spoon half of tomato mixture evenly over eggplant slices.
Repeat procedure with remaining eggplant slices and tomato mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 425 degrees for 45 minutes, or until golden.
Makes 4 servings, each 1 cup.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling and pineapple into a 9 by 13 inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Melt butter and pour over. Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In a bowl, combine chilies, tomatoes, onions, cilantro, jalapeno and garlic. In another bowl, combine vinegar, oil, pepper and salt if desired; stir into vegetable mixture. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours. This has 2 grams carbohydrate.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in large bowl with sealproof lid, then set aside.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into oiled 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown the meat and onions.
Cook over medium heat until the onion is tender.
Stir in seasonings, tomatoes, soup and rice. Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into a baking dish and top with cheese strips.
Broil until the cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Mix rice, soups and water together and put into lightly greased baking pan.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
DON'T PEEK.
Cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans with cold water and add soda; bring to a boil. Drain; add fresh water and bring to a boil again; drain.
Add water again and boil beans 1 hour or until tender.
Drain.
Place in baking pan.
Add rest of the ingredients and bake until not soupy or about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with cooking spray. Combine all of the ingredients, except the crackers and butter. Pour into the prepared dish.
Crush crackers; toss with melted butter.
Sprinkle the crumbs over the vegetables.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all together, then mix in 1/2 can dried onions.
Cook at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove.
Put 1/2 can dried onions on top.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: sour cream bake casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Cook hamburger and onion; drain. Mix all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Spread Cheddar cheese on top.

title: cheddar-style broccoli
directions: Wash and trim broccoli; split heavy stalks.
Place water and salt in saucepan; bring to boiling point.
Add broccoli; cover and bring to a boil again.
Reduce heat; cook for 10 to 20 minutes or until tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat; add cheese.
Toss lightly; serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: If using peaches, drain juice.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: In a 2-quart microproof casserole, combine juices, spices and sugar.
Cook, covered, on High for 9 to 11 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Strain and garnish with orange slices. Makes 8 servings.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells (makes 2 pies).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk and heat thoroughly.
Add cheese until melted. Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crescent dinner roll snacks
directions: Roll out crescent rolls into 4 rectangular shapes (instead of 8 triangles).
Spread with your favorite flavor of mustard.
Top with your choice of thin sliced deli meats, then top with grated cheddar cheese.
Roll up jellyroll fashion - cut into 5 slices. Bake according to directions on dinner roll pkg.
Makes 20 snacks. These are quick to make and freeze easily.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat until fluffy cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shells and sprinkle top with chopped peanuts.
Freeze.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown
beef
and onions.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve with Doritos or taco chips.
Decorate with tomato wedges, if desired.
Use large bowl!

title: pierogi
directions: Mix flour, butter, salt and 4 eggs in a large mixing bowl. Add water until proper consistency for dough.
Mix cheese, 4 more eggs and cooked potatoes, mashing them until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll dough and add cheese mixture.
Cut out and crimp edges.
Place in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: emerald salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in square glass dish. Refrigerate and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine Bisquick and sausage together.
Then add cheese and milk;
mix well.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 60.

title: baked raccoon
directions: Sprinkle raccoon well with tenderizer.
Let set in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Remove from the refrigerator, place in a big pot and parboil.
Take out of pot and place in a large baking pan.
Put all of the ingredients on the raccoon except the potatoes.
Place in a 325° oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Put the potatoes all around the raccoon and let bake 1/2 hour or until raccoon is brown.

title: squa corn
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off fat.
Drain juice from corn.
Dice cheese.
Mix all ingredients together in pot and simmer on stove until cheese melts, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk and add frozen Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Add remaining pudding.
Top with a layer of crackers.
Mix can of frosting with 3 teaspoons milk.
Spread on top.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Can be frozen.
Other flavors of pudding may be used.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in plastic food bag.
Mix well. Grease a 10 x 15-inch pan. Dredge chicken in dry mixture.
Place in pan, skin side up. Melt butter and drizzle over top. Bake at 375°, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: potatoes - scalloped
directions: Combine the potatoes, onions, flour, salt, pepper and parsley flakes in bowl.
Put in greased, shallow baking dish.
Scald milk. Pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and salt together before pouring over first 5 ingredients.
Drain some of the liquid before serving.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.
Salad will keep 1 to 2 weeks in refrigerator, tightly covered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Form into a ball.

title: 6 minute strawberry preserves
directions: Cover with boiling water 1 minute, then drain. Put into preserving kettle with 2 cups sugar. Boil rapidly 3 minutes. Add 2 more cups sugar and boil hard for 3 minutes. Skim. Let stand overnight, uncovered. Put into jars and seal without heating.

title: twinkie surprise
directions: Slice Twinkies in halves lengthwise.
Put in 13 x 9 x 1-inch pan.
Pour thawed strawberries over Twinkies.
In a large bowl, mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour over the strawberries. Cover with Saran Wrap and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: crock-pot ravioli
directions: Cook the noodles to al dente stage; drain.
Brown meats and onion; drain. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and Italian seasoning. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Put half of the noodles in buttered crock-pot. Top with half of the meat mixture. Top meat mixture with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and 1 cup sour cream.
Repeat layers. Cook in crock-pot until hot and bubbly.

title: mile high pie(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Place in a large glass bowl (do not use plastic or metal bowls).
Beat together the strawberries (thawed), sugar and egg whites for 15 minutes with a power beater (either electric or battery).
The mixture will be stiff, but not as stiff as meringue. Slowly fold in Cool Whip until completely blended.
Place in crusts; freeze for 3 to 4 hours.
Can be served frozen.
Can be kept in freezer for several weeks.

title: pina frijole salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice for dressing. (Reserve remaining juice for other uses.)
Chill pineapple until ready to use.
Combine reserved 1/2 cup juice, olive oil, vinegar, onion, pickles, sugar, chili powder, Tabasco, kidney beans and celery.
Marinate overnight.
Just before serving, place lettuce in salad bowl.
Line sides with pineapple slices.
Pour kidney bean mixture in center.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Toss before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add red food coloring and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add cake flour with the 2 teaspoons of cocoa alternately with the buttermilk.
Beat well!!
Add the baking soda to the vinegar and add immediately to the cake batter.
Beat well. Pour into two 9-inch layer (round) pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost.

title: creamy fudge squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 9-inch square pan with foil. Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread over prepared crust.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Lift fudge from pan onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store, covered, in refrigerator (prep time:
15 minutes).

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Set out cream cheese until soft; thaw strawberries and Cool Whip. Mix sugar and cream cheese. Add strawberries, drained pineapple and pecans. Fold in Cool Whip. Put in freezer. Remove 1/2 hour before serving. Can be refrozen.

title: goulash
directions: Boil macaroni; drain well.
Brown ground beef; add chili powder and salt.
Mix with macaroni.
Add to cheese, onion and pepper. Place in greased baking dish and cover with 1 can tomato soup. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and cream in large pan; bring mixture to a boil and let boil 10 to 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then stir in marshmallow cream, stirring until fluffy looking and stiff. Pour immediately onto well buttered plates to cool.
Makes about 3 to 4 plates of fudge.
Cut in pieces to serve.

title: mexican chicken chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and simmer until flavors are blended well.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Chill.

title: granny's banana pudding
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix; beat at low speed 1 minute.
Layer 1/3 of pudding mixture, half of wafers and half of bananas in 1 1/2-quart serving bowl; repeat layers.
Top with remaining pudding.
Cover surface with plastic wrap; chill.
Garnish top with crushed wafers. Serve with whipped cream.

title: creamy dijon dressing
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Add mayonnaise and chill.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and butter.
Beat.
Add cocoa and flour; fold in pecans, vanilla and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (9 x 13-inch pan).
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with toothpick and spread with one jar marshmallow cream or until cake is covered.
Let cool.

title: rice and peas
directions: Soak beans in
water
overnight.
In
large
pot, place beans in pot with
quarts
water
and cook over medium heat until they are tender enough to crush with the fingers (2 to 3 hours). Meanwhile, in a heavy skillet, add oil, brown onions, and seasoning with
salted
pork.
Also,
add
one
cup of hot water to grated
coconut	and
squeeze
out
cream
through
a strainer. Save cream
and discard pulp.
To previously cooked peas, add coconut
cream
and
seasoning.
Bring to a boil and add rice. Cook over
medium heat until rice is cooked and all the water is absorbed, adding more water if necessary.
Serve fish, chicken or beef.
(Good with stew.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
In another bowl, combine stuffing and batter.
Spread 1/2 of the stuffing in the bottom of a 12 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon on the vegetable mixture.
Add remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: best ever strawberry pie
directions: Pie Crust:
Mix Bisquick, melted butter and water into pie plate with fork.
Pat into shape.
Poke holes into crust.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes until brown.

title: peanut orange balls
directions: Combine chopped peanuts, orange slices (diced) and coconut in large mixing bowl.
Add sweetened condensed milk, mixing well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: cheesy beef pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Sprinkle with cornstarch; blend.
Add taco sauce, parsley and mushrooms.
Spread 1/2 beaten egg whites over bottom crust.
Spoon meat into pie shell; sprinkle with cheese.
Pour remaining egg whites over cheese. Add top crust and brush with slightly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In a large bowl, stir together dry cake mix, pie filling, vanilla and eggs until well blended. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake in preheated oven 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely. Frost with Easy Chocolate Cherry Frosting.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix the crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted oleo together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; let cool.
Blend together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hearty clam chowder(old chesapeake bay style)
directions: Saute pork in large pot.
Remove and set aside.
Add onions and bell pepper; saute.
Add reserved pork and remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to cover potatoes, 1 or 2 chopped carrots, may be added with potatoes for color.
Cook until tender. Add clam juice; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: ralph's "dog" biscuits
directions: Mix
ingredients
with about 1/2 cup cold water.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Dough
should
form a ball.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut
into any shape you like, even dog bones.
Bake on lightly, greased cookie sheet for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Cool on rack.

title: pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, baking powder, flour and milk; pour over melted butter in deep pan (do not stir).
Pour fruit on top of batter (do not stir).
Use 3/4 cup sugar over fruit if not sweet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: coconut pies
directions: Soak coconut in the milk for about 15 minutes.
Pour off milk from coconut.
Mix with all the other ingredients and pour into the two pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chilli beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions. Cook until done. Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain off grease. Add all other ingredients, then let simmer for 30 minutes. Great with bread.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and put into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 370° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: rich pecan pie(8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine syrup, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil gently 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place pecans in pie shell. Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in a bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool.
Serve with Mapley Whipped Cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour; measure and add baking powder, soda and salt. Sift again.
Cream shortening; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Combine thoroughly but do not beat.
Bake in greased and lined bread pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken jazz
directions: Layer chicken, cheese, soup mixture and stuffing in order listed.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Cut off excess fat from steak. Cut steak into serving-size slices. Roll slices in flour mix. In large skillet, brown sliced steak in oil.

Drain and place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Top with celery, onion and mushrooms. Combine water, garlic and steak sauce; pour over mushrooms in pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Serves 6.

title: cheese olives
directions: Work cheese and flour together.
Add melted margarine and mix well.
Mold about 1 teaspoon of cheese dough around each olive. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased tray.
Refrigerate for an hour or more.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Layer ingredients in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: ham rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
On work surface, stretch pizza dough into 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
In a small bowl, whisk yogurt and mustard together; spread mixture over dough to cover, leaving 1 1/2-inch border.
Arrange ham over dough; sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Starting from wide end, roll dough jelly roll fashion to enclose filling.
Pinch seams to seal.

title: chocolate cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix and cook together for one minute the sugar, butter and milk.
Remove from heat and add cocoa, oats and nuts.
Add vanilla and stir until it can be dropped from a spoon onto wax paper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together in order given.
Roll into teaspoon size balls. Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 9 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: twenty minute apple butter
directions: Cook for 20 minutes after bringing to rolling boil.

title: pirogi casserole
directions: Boil lasagna noodles, cooked al dente, for 10 to 12 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Saute butter and onions.
Prepare instant potatoes according to directions on the box.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. When vegetables are soft, add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, soups and broth. Heat thoroughly, then add the Velveeta cheese. When serving, add the chips.

title: dens french dressing
directions: Blend in blender and store in refrigerator.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans, then place in pan to boil with plenty of water. Add onion powder, garlic powder and beef flavor bouillon cubes when beans are fully cooked.
Cut up onions into small pieces and fry in olive oil until lightly brown.
Pour over beans and boil again.
Add salt to taste.

title: sara salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: mexican corn bake
directions: Place cheese, margarine, evaporated milk, garlic salt and red pepper in small Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring until blended.
Add corn and chiles, mixing well. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, together in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans and peas.
Add remaining ingredients. Marinate overnight.
Drain all juices and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: butter pecan date bars
directions: Mix chopped dates and half of pecans with half box of dry cake mix.
Set aside.
Add eggs, brown sugar and water to other half of cake mix.
Beat well; stir in other half of cake mix.
Bake in a greased and floured jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, spread with a can of butter pecan frosting mix.
Top with pecans.

title: horehound drops
directions: Boil horehound and water until mixture is reduce to half.
Then combine the other ingredients to liquid mixture.
Boil to hard crack stage and pour onto well-greased cookie sheet or marble slab. When cool, break into pieces.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a fork.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crumble crackers; alternate vegetables and crackers.
Top with mayonnaise; spread over top, then add bottle of Ranch dressing. Do not stir!

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make pastry for 2 pie crust (makes 6 dumplings).
Core and peel 6 apples.
Roll and cut pastry to wrap each apple.
Fill each apple cavity with a mixture of:
1/2 cup sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, and 1 teaspoon butter.
Wrap each apple and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil together for 3 minutes:
1 cup sugar, water, 3 tablespoons butter and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over apples. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned applesauce stack cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well. Stir in vanilla, corn syrup and buttermilk.
Sift together the spices, baking powder, soda and 3 cups of the flour.
Add gradually to creamed mixture, beating smooth each time.
Knead in more flour slowly to make stiff dough.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut in circles the size of dinner plate.
Bake each layer at 425° until golden brown.
Cover each layer liberally with applesauce before adding next layer.
Let cake stand at room temperature until cold; wrap well in heavy foil and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and then add all ingredients; stir well.

title: happiness cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, margarine and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Add chocolate syrup and flour and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured fluted tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until cake tests done with a toothpick.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High 11 to 13 minutes, stirring well at 4-minute intervals.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until melted.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 dish and chill two hours.
Cut into one-inch squares.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil all meat together in a large pot. Shred meat after it's cooked. Add back to meat broth. Add potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer all day. (The longer it cooks, the better it gets!) Stir.

title: susie e.'s spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together well.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: watkins cupcakes
directions: Cream butter; slowly add sugar, then beaten egg yolks. Alternately add milk and flour, baking powder, well beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Center may be partly taken out and filled with whipped cream.
Replace with top of cake.
Cover with boiled white frosting and shredded coconut.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the blueberries.
Stir in the blueberries by hand after the other ingredients are all mixed.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pear up
directions: Cut 1 pear in slices, not too thin.
Cut out center.
Put Cool Whip in center of pear.
Put cherry in center of Cool Whip. Enjoy!!

title: taco dip
directions: Layer #1:
Mix together bean dip and plain refried beans. Spread on plate.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour, salt and butter together.
Slowly add scalded milk, then add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn oven back to 375° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hash brown scallop
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine hash browns, shredded cheese and sliced onions. Dissolve chicken bouillon cube in 1/2 cup boiling water; pour over potato mixture. Dot with 1 tablespoon butter or margarine. Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring gently once or twice. Top with American cheese and bake 1 to 2 minutes more, until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Combine slaw and onions.
Toast sunflower seeds, almonds and crushed Ramen noodles.

title: fuzzy navel
directions: Mix in glass over ice.

title: honey bread
directions: Dissolve and proof yeast in 1 cup warm water; add 1 tablespoon honey to yeast water and let foam.
Stir 1 1/2 cups hot water, salt and butter until butter melts; add honey.
Add yeast and all mixtures together in large bowl.
Add flour a cup at a time, stirring.
Knead dough 5 to 10 minutes until smooth; grease bowl and dough.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Boil sugar and orange juice together until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add grated orange rind and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Pour out and break into pecan halves.

title: peanut butter, bacon appetizer
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Toast white bread, rounds, triangles or square.
Spread with peanut butter.
Crumble bacon on top.
Run under broiler for 1 minute.
Serve hot with cocktails.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Use a pan a little bigger than 9x13, if you don't it will boil over.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Mix in shortening thoroughly and orange rind and juice. Add beaten egg. Fold in cranberries. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick stuck into center comes out clean, for 1 hour.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Brown
in
skillet,
hamburger, salt, pepper and onion. Add catsup
and
grated cheese.
Cook until melted.
Let cool and
put on
hamburger buns.
Wrap in tinfoil and put in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snax
directions: Melt margarine in a large roaster or dishpan.
Add Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Add garlic salt, Season-All and celery salt; mix well.
Add 1 pound salted peanuts; mix thoroughly to coat nuts with mixture.
Add Kix, Cheerios, Corn Chex and Rice Chex.
Mix well.
Heat oven or electric roaster to 250°.
Cook mixture for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in empty cereal boxes or sealed jars or cans.

title: picante sauce
directions: Simmer 3 to 4 hours. Pack in hot jars and place in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda; add oil and sugar substitutes and mix well. Beat eggs; add mashed bananas and other ingredients. Beat until well mixed. Pour into a 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef curry
directions: Melt butter and oil in large saucepan.
Add meat; brown quickly.
Remove from pan.
Fry onions in remaining fat until soft.
Add the garlic and curry powder; cook gently 2 minutes. Replace meat and add beef broth, puree, chutney, lemon juice and yogurt.
Simmer until tender.
Serve with rice, chopped peppers, tomatoes, coconut and peanuts, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a bread pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: overnight refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs, salt and half cup of flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Cover tightly and store overnight.
When ready to use, punch dough and shape into medium balls.
Let rise about 2 hours. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in buttered casserole dish.
Crumble crackers over the top and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, chocolate and salt; mix well.
Add milk gradually; heat over low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Cover and continue cooking 8 minutes; stir occasionally.
In mixing bowl, gradually stir half of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; return to saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked shell; refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: gute nudelyn (noodles)
directions: Beat eggs well. Add milk and beat well.
Add baking powder and salt. Knead in about 2 cups flour to make a stiff dough. Take small portions of dough and on a floured surface, roll out in thin sheet.
Cut into narrow strips. Set aside 2 hours to dry.

title: broiled pear salad
directions: Heat broiler.
Brush each half pear with 1/2 teaspoon honey. Broil 2 minutes or until slightly soft.
Combine butter with remaining honey.
Spoon onto pear halves.
Arrange strawberry slices on top.
Garnish with mint leaves, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lithuanian garlic bread
directions: Melt butter over very low heat.
Add olive oil and softened garlic.
Saute for a minute or two, but don't let it brown.
Add Italian seasoning and remove from heat.
Dip cut rolls in mixture; put on a cookie sheet and sprinkle with garlic powder, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Broil under low flame for a few minutes, but keep watching.
It burns very quickly.

title: christmas cider
directions: Heat cider to boiling.
Lower heat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Strain and serve.

title: rice and shrimp salad
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except artichoke hearts.
Mix well.
Add artichoke hearts and toss lightly.
Chill. Top with sliced hard-boiled eggs, if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into bowl.
Beat eggs until thick and light colored.
Add water and oil to eggs.
Combine with dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add pumpkin.
Bake at 350° in 3 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Whip the cream, add sugar and flour.
Mix egg yolks and vanilla together.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch pans that are lightly greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. After baked poke holes in cake and pour coconut milk on cake.
Let cool, then ice with topping below.

title: blackberry cake or muffins
directions: Mix together the sugar, butter and eggs; set aside.
In a cup, mix together the soda and cocoa, then fill the cup up with 1/2 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Add alternating flour, allspice, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add blackberries.
Bake at 350°.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: Mix in blender half of the sugar, all of the eggs and bourbon. Let stand 4 hours.
Add milk, condensed milk and rest of the sugar.
Mix.
Whip the cream and soften ice cream.
Add to mixture.

title: easy chinese sukiyaki
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Put celery, onion and pepper in pan with tight lid and cook over moderate (warm) heat for 15 minutes.
(Check on them; want veggies crunchy.)
Combine vegetables with soup, bean sprouts, mushrooms, burger and water mixed with bouillon cube and cornstarch.
Heat through.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce; toss until well mixed. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and chill. Serve with dinner rolls, or on lettuce.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 325 for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuff shells
directions: Cook shells
and
drain.
Brown
hamburger
and
drain. Grate Cheddar cheese and mix in cool hamburger.
Mix small can of tomato sauce
in hamburger, then add and mix Ricotta cheese with hamburger
mixture.
Stuff	shells with mixture, place in baking pan.
Pour	spaghetti sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread into oblong pan.
Beat well the cream cheese, 2 eggs and sugar.
Spread over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until light brown on top and cake tests done.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix fresh milk, canned milk and baking soda together.
Cream sugar and shortening; add orange juice, salt, milk, soda, baking powder and flour.
Add flour a cup at a time.
Mix until just holds shape.
(May not need all flour if oranges are small.)
Will still be a little sticky.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container.
Mix periodically.

title: berry punch
directions: How to make:
Combine gelatin and sugar.
Put kettle on burner. Put about 2 1/2 cups of water into tea kettle. Turn burner on high heat.
When water boils turn off burner.
Pour 2 cups of boiling water into bowl with gelatin mixture.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in 2 cups cold water, the frozen berries and the lemonade concentrate.
Stir until berries and lemonade thaw. Chill mixture until needed, then put lemon lime beverage in.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread slices in 1/2 cup water; add eggs and mix well. Add ground chuck, cheese, salt, pepper and oregano and mix well. Form meat mixture in small balls and brown slowly in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Add meatballs to sauce and cook for 30 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch slaw
directions: Combine first two ingredients and let stand for two hours, then drain.
Combine last five ingredients and boil 15 minutes. Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Good for several weeks.

title: salsa
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until flavors are blended, at least 30 minutes.
Yield:
3/4 cup.

title: zucchini-walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Soften cheese and spread on platter.
Spread on sauce, then sprinkle on shrimp, diced tomato, ripe olives (sliced) and then cheese.
Serve with firm crackers.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain fruit juice.
Add enough water to make 2 cups liquid. Heat to boiling and prepare Jell-O.
Add fruit and nuts.
Add Coke last.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Pat meat around the sides and bottom of a deep dish casserole. Use as you would a crust.
Pour potatoes, carrots and beans into center.
Add seasoning.
Pour soup over all. Bake at 350° until meat is done.
You may top with cheese, if so desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put Tater
Tots on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish, then add
browned
meat.
Mix the soups and water together and pour over
top.	Sprinkle 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil brown sugar, butter and syrup.
Boil 5 minutes, then add cream of tartar.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Pour over popped corn and nuts and stir.
Bake in 2 sheet pans for 1 hour at 225°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: yummy bars
directions: Bring syrup, sugar and margarine to a boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Stir cornflakes into mixture until well blended.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together in a pan.
Pour on top of mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed grape leaves(warak areesh)
directions: Allow a little fat to remain on the meat if you are grinding it.
Wash rice in cold water, drain, cover with water, rinse again and drain well.
Add all seasonings to rice; mix thoroughly.
Rub butter into meat.
Combine meat and rice by rubbing rice and all seasonings well into meat; check seasonings.

title: banana delight
directions: Mix instant pudding, condensed milk and milk together for 2 minutes. Refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes. Whip whipping cream. Add whipped cream, sour cream and pudding mixture together. In large dish, place layer of vanilla wafers, layer of sliced bananas and half of the mixture. Repeat each layer.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crust Oreo cookies.
Save 1 cup cookie mix.
Spread in pan. Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Whip the cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups milk together.
Add pudding and rest of milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over Oreo cookie mix (already in pan).
Pour remainder of crushed cookies over top.
May also be layered in a clean flowerpot and served, garnished with a flower.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend well.
(Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.)
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each with fork.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: raisin squares
directions: Put the pie crusts into a 9 x 12 pan to cover the bottom. Cook raisins in water until plump.
Add sugar, spices, salt and lemon juices.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Pour into 9 x 12 pan and seal crust.
Sprinkle lightly with milk.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown.

title: swedish cabbage rolls(crock-pot)
directions: Place cabbage leaves in boiling water, about 3 or 4 minutes. The leaves should be limp.
Drain.
In medium size bowl, in center of each cabbage leaf, put about 1/4 meat mixture.
Fold cabbage leaf sides in over meat mixture and then roll the cabbage ends of the leaf over the mixture.
Put in crock-pot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Continue beating until smooth. Spoon filling into prepared crust.
Freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: mother's sweetheart cookies
directions: Beat together butter and cream cheese until creamy. Add sugar and vanilla. Beat again. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamy mixture. Stir in oats and nuts. Mix well. Chill overnight.

title: christmas pound cake
directions: Beat egg yolks; mix sugar and baking powder together.
Add to egg yolks.
Add vanilla and fold in sifted flour.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Beat egg whites and add to mixture.
Stir together and bake in a tube pan for 2 hours at 250° or bake in loaf pan until done (1 hour).

title: french butter cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add powdered sugar gradually. Continue to cream.
Add salt, vanilla and egg.
Beat thoroughly. Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well. Chill at least 10 minutes.
Form into 1/2-inch balls and flatten with fork on sheet. Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: creamy stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery and cut into 3-inch pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Stuff celery pieces with cream cheese mixture.
Makes 9 pieces.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda. Pour over 6 to 7 quarts of popped corn; stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine Bisquick, cheese and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet (using Pam is optional).
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine butter and garlic. Brush on biscuits and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put chicken or tuna, celery, salt, grated onion, mayonnaise and lemon juice in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
If milder sauce is desired, omit hot pepper sauce.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together in large bowl; set aside.
Layer bottom of large casserole dish with vanilla wafers and 1/2 of bananas.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions in separate bowl.
Mix together with Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip mixture.
Pour 1/2 of mixture on top of vanilla wafers and bananas.
Add another layer of vanilla wafers and bananas; pour remaining mixture on top.
Garnish with vanilla wafers around edges of bowl.
Chill.

title: shrimp and chili in a blanket
directions: Mix chili sauce and garlic; pour over shrimp in glass bowl. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Arrange 1/3 of the bacon pieces in single layer on paper towel-lined 10-inch plate; top with paper towel and another 1/3 of the bacon.
Top with paper towel.
Arrange remaining bacon on top; cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes or until partially cooked.
Wrap bacon piece around each shrimp; secure with wooden pick.
Arrange 10 shrimp in circle on paper-towel lined plate.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave one plate at a time on High 3 to 4 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Makes 20 appetizers.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pan(s).
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Mash bananas and stir in sour cream.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to sugar/shortening alternating with adding banana and sour cream mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together but egg whites.
Mix well.
Fold egg whites in mixture.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until firm in center.

title: *little porcupines
directions: Mix together beef, rice, baking powder, onion, salt and parsley.
Mold into firm balls, about 1 1/4-inches in diameter. Brown in 3 tablespoons fat, turning frequently.
After browning meat balls, pour tomato soup over them.
Cook in covered skillet, over low heat, until rice is tender and stands out on meat.
This quantity makes 7 meat balls.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage 8 minutes in salt water; drain.
Cook onion and pepper in bacon grease.
Toss bread in melted butter.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in 1 tablespoon lard until crumbly. Add water and mix until a soft dough forms. Knead until dough is smooth and springy in texture. Make into 12 balls. Melt 1 tablespoon lard and brush on each ball of dough. Set aside for 30 to 45 minutes. On a lightly floured surface, roll ball to a 4-inch circle. Then stretch to 7 to 8-inches in diameter. Poke hole in center. Fry in oil at 365° until lightly browned, turning once. Serve hot with butter and/or honey.

title: scalloped potatoes with mushrooms
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Alternate potatoes and onions.
Pour soup over top.
Pour water to top of dish.
Sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb crunch-lancaster county style
directions: Mix together rhubarb, sugar and flour.
Put this in 6 x 10 greased casserole.
On top of this mixture, put brown sugar, oatmeal, flour and butter which has been mixed together!
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat egg until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla and stir until smooth.
Quickly stir in salt, soda and flour.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased pan. Bake at 350° about 7 to 9 minutes or until edges are slightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: special party dip
directions: Blend cheese and cream until smooth.
Add French dressing, ketchup, onion and salt.
Mix well.
Place in serving bowl. Serve with chips, crackers or cut up vegetables.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: mini peanut butter cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches, with paper baking cups.
Place 1 wafer, flat side down in each cup.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in medium bowl until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Fill cups three-fourths full.
Press peanut butter cups in center.
Bake about 20 minutes until centers are firm; cool 15 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut. Chill. Reserve 1 cup of mixture for top frosting. Spread remainder between layers of cake. Combine reserved sour cream mixture with 8 ounces Cool Whip. Blend until smooth and spread on top and sides of cake. If desired, save some coconut to sprinkle on top. Seal cake in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: cereal date nut cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour and baking soda. Add cut up dates.
Add pecan halves.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: sally ann's
directions: Combine all ingredients. Form dough into
rolls and refrigerate overnight. Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Stores well in airtight container or in freezer.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat margarine and water on low heat.
Add flour a little at a time until it gets thick (on low heat).
Cool.
Put flour mixture in a bowl; beat in 4 eggs (one at a time) with mixer. Grease 9 x 13-inch tin pan with margarine.
Spread mixture in pan (put up sides of pan a little bit).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
It will puff.

title: pork pie(new year's kreatopita)
directions: Place 1/4 pound butter, ground pork and onions in pan and brown.
Add water; continue to simmer for 45 minutes.
Set meat mixture aside to cool.
Beat the eggs slightly; add tapioca.
Mix well and fold into meat mixture.
Place 5 pastry sheets, buttering each, on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 of meat mixture; top with 5 more buttered pastry sheets.
Spread remaining meat mixture.
Sterilize "good luck coin" (a quarter or fifty-cent piece) and place among pastry sheets.
Place 5 buttered pastry sheets over last layer of meat mixture; pour remaining butter over entire "kreatopita."

title: snow candy
directions: Melt candy in a double boiler. Can be put in microwave, broken down and stirred 2 to 3 times. After melted, add nuts and cereal. Mix well. Spoon onto waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm. Store in airtight container.

title: yorkshire trifle
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O, place fruit in deep dish and cover with fruit swirls.
Then pour the Jell-O over fruit and fruit swirls (when set).
Pour vanilla pudding on top.
Whip heavy cream and place on top, then cover with sprinkles and keep refrigerated. Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil until smooth.
Stir constantly.
Add 3 1/2 cups powdered sugar while warm.
Beat well.

title: batter fried pumpkin or squash blossoms
directions: Two to three dozen blossoms makes 8 servings.
Blossoms will keep two to three days placed in a large bowl of water in refrigerator.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Divide chips and cheese, 1 cup to each portion.
Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, salad dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 meat mixture in 2-quart casserole with 1 portion of cheese-chip mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix in a large container which may be used for freezing.
(I use a 1-gallon plastic, clean milk carton.)
Tint before freezing. May use any color (red, green, yellow).
Remember, tint slightly darker than you want final mixture.
Chill 2
liter Sprite, ginger ale or 7-Up.
Two hours before serving, remove concentrate from freezer.
Cut top from plastic jug.
You desire to have frozen slush when you combine Sprite and concentrate.
Serves 40 punch cups.
Wonderful tart punch with iced cake, like wedding cake.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed and set aside.
Slice/chop zucchini, carrots and broccoli.
Chop artichoke hearts if whole.
Cut cheese into bite size pieces or crumble.
Blanch zucchini, carrots and broccoli. Put into boiling water for 5 seconds; remove and rinse with cold water until cool.
Put everything into
a large bowl with the pasta and add pesto; mix well to coat everything.
Best when served cold.
Enjoy!

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes for 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in casserole dish. Mix soup with 1/2 cup of water.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven until potatoes are done at 350°.
When done, put cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Place frozen fish in bottom of large saucepan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over fish.
Boil until done (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Serve with melted butter.
Tastes just like lobster.

title: ground meat cornbread casserole
directions: Season ground meat according to your taste.
Fry until all redness is gone, and drain any fat.
Prepare cornbread mix according to instructions on package.
Add can of cream-style corn to cornbread mix and mix well into batter.

title: cake for anything(with buttercream filling)
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, using only half of the cheese.
Mix well.
Spread into 9 inch baking dish and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit-filled breakfast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, mixing well.
Add flour and mix with a fork until of pastry consistency.
Remove 1/4 of pastry and set aside.
Press remaining dough over the bottom and sides of a 10 x 15-inch baking sheet. Spread jam over dough and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Crumble reserved pastry mix over the jam.
Bake 30 minutes; cool 5 to 10 minutes and cut into squares while warm.
Makes about 60.

title: cold fudge sunday cake
directions: Mix pecans, flour and margarine until like pie dough and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on; skin and dice.
Dice fine the onion.
Add seasonings; sprinkle each as you would for each potato.
Cook bacon, drain and cut in small pieces.
Use 1/3 cup bacon grease to each 2/3 cup vinegar (1 cup per each 6 to 10 medium potatoes).
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons sugar per cup of liquid. Heat liquid to blend flavors.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir in bacon, leaving some crumbled for garnish.

title: hormel chili dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese in the bottom of a Pyrex dish.
Place a layer of chili, then a layer of grated sharp cheese.
Bake on 350° until dip bubbles.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dump pineapple and swirl to fill in corners.
Next, dump in pie filling and smooth out to cover pineapple.
Dump dry cake mix on top to cover fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts. Cut butter into "pats" and arrange on top of cake mix. Do not mix.
Bake 1 hour (until brown) at 350°.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook until thick flour and milk.
Beat together until like whip cream the butter or shortening, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Add cooked mixture and beat until fluffy at high speed on electric mixer.
Will frost two 9-inch layers.

title: chili
directions: Simmer all the ingredients 1 hour.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese, chopped onion and crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover first 4 ingredients with water and boil in soup pot until tender.
Whip eggs by hand and keep adding flour until crumbly and dry.
Add to soup pot and cook until tender. Add bacon bits and grease to soup pot.
Add milk to desired thickness.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Place skin down in a foil lined pan.
Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover; turn down to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, until tender and brown.
(Great with pork chops.)

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese, stuffing mix and butter. Put in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix stuffing mix and butter and put on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pizza grilled cheese
directions: Butter one side of each slice of bread. Place one slice in a skillet, butter side down. Top with cheese, pepperoni, sauce and second slice of bread, butter side up. Cook over medium heat until golden brown, turning once.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut a split down middle of wieners; place a cheese stick in each.
Wrap a crescent roll layer around each.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° until lightly golden brown.
Maybe sliced after cooled or served whole topped with hot chili.

title: maine fish chowder
directions: Skin and bone fish; cut meat into small pieces about 1-inch long.
Slice the potatoes; boil in 1 quart water.
Mash potatoes, then return them to the water in which they were boiled.
Chop the salt pork; saute in frying pan.
When fairly crisp, add the diced onions.
When onions are soft, add fish.
Fry slowly until fish begins to flake.
Add mashed potatoes with the water, sugar, salt and pepper, cream and curry powder.
Just before serving, sprinkle the chowder liberally with crushed oyster cracker crumbs.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake until firm.

title: grandmom's banana nut bread
directions: Cream together eggs and brown sugar.
Add buttermilk and bananas.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in wax paper-lined 7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan in 350° for 1 hour.
Use toothpick to test for doneness. Cool before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan:
sugar, Pet milk, marshmallows, butter or margarine and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a full boil.
Boil and stir 5 full minutes.
Take off heat; stir in until completely melted, chocolate chips.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Cool in buttered 8-inch pan.

title: jolopes
directions: Cook chicken with onion, carrot and parsley.
Grease casserole.
Layer:
3 tortillas, shredded chicken, 1 can soup, chillies, sour cream and layer each of cheese.
Repeat 2 or 3 times.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Cut bologna into hunks; put into container you will want to keep it in.
Fill with a diluted vinegar solution (2 to 1; 2 parts vinegar to 1 part water).
This way, you know you have enough to cover the bologna when you finish.
Pour off vinegar water solution into pan.
Add the sugar, bay leaves and spices; heat and pour over bologna in jar.
Let cool.
Refrigerate for about 3 days.

title: trifle
directions: Put in a large bowl and layer the angel food cake, thawed frozen strawberries, sliced bananas and crushed pineapple. Repeat layers.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Pour heavy cream in saucepan.
Cook, stirring frequently, on medium to low heat. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking until cream begins to thicken slightly.
Add grated cheese and continue cooking until mixture is just slightly thick.

title: creamy pasta primavera
directions: Saute vegetables in 1/4 cup margarine.
Add cream cheese and milk; stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in ham and Parmesan cheese.
Toss spaghetti with remaining margarine. Add cream cheese mixture; mix lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
